fields.name: MODE
fields.desc: This bits decides which one operation mode will be used. 3'd0: AES-EN-128, 3'd1: AES-EN-192, 3'd2: AES-EN-256, 3'd4: AES-DE-128, 3'd5: AES-DE-192, 3'd6: AES-DE-256.

fields.name: ENDIAN
fields.desc: endian. [1:0] key endian, [3:2] text_in endian or in_stream endian,  [5:4] text_out endian or out_stream endian

fields.name: TRIGGER
fields.desc: Set this bit to start AES calculation.

fields.name: STATE
fields.desc: Those bits shows AES status. For typical AES, 0: idle, 1: busy. For DMA-AES, 0: idle, 1: busy, 2: calculation_done.

fields.name: BLOCK_MODE
fields.desc: Those bits decides which block mode will be used. 0x0: ECB, 0x1: CBC, 0x2: OFB, 0x3: CTR, 0x4: CFB-8, 0x5: CFB-128, 0x6: GCM, 0x7: reserved.

fields.name: BLOCK_NUM
fields.desc: Those bits stores the number of Plaintext/ciphertext block.

fields.name: INC_SEL
fields.desc: This bit decides the standard incrementing function. 0: INC32. 1: INC128.

fields.desc: Set this bit to continue GCM operation.

fields.name: INT_CLEAR
fields.desc: Set this bit to clear the AES interrupt.

fields.name: INT_ENA
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable interrupt that occurs when DMA-AES calculation is done.

fields.name: DATE
fields.desc: This bits stores the version information of AES.

fields.name: DMA_EXIT
fields.desc: Set this register to leave calculation done stage. Recommend to use it after software finishes reading DMA's output buffer.

fields.name: IN_DONE_CH_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when the last data pointed by one inlink descriptor has been received for Rx channel 0.

fields.name: IN_SUC_EOF_CH_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when the last data pointed by one inlink descriptor has been received for Rx channel 0. For UHCI0 the raw interrupt bit turns to high level when the last data pointed by one inlink descriptor has been received and no data error is detected for Rx channel 0.

fields.name: IN_ERR_EOF_CH_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when data error is detected only in the case that the peripheral is UHCI0 for Rx channel 0. For other peripherals this raw interrupt is reserved.

fields.name: IN_DSCR_ERR_CH_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when detecting inlink descriptor error including owner error and the second and third word error of inlink descriptor for Rx channel 0.

fields.name: IN_DSCR_EMPTY_CH_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when Rx buffer pointed by inlink is full and receiving data is not completed but there is no more inlink for Rx channel 0.

fields.name: INFIFO_OVF_CH_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This raw interrupt bit turns to high level when level 1 fifo of Rx channel 0 is overflow.

fields.name: INFIFO_UDF_CH_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This raw interrupt bit turns to high level when level 1 fifo of Rx channel 0 is underflow.

fields.name: LOCK_ENA
fields.desc: The bit is used to enable lock operation. It will be cleared by hardware after lock operation done. Note that (1) this bit and unlock_ena bit are mutually exclusive, that is, those bits can not be set to 1 at the same time. (2) lock operation can be applied on LL1-ICache, L1-DCache and L2-Cache.

fields.name: UNLOCK_ENA
fields.desc: The bit is used to enable unlock operation. It will be cleared by hardware after unlock operation done. Note that (1) this bit and lock_ena bit are mutually exclusive, that is, those bits can not be set to 1 at the same time. (2) unlock operation can be applied on L1-ICache, L1-DCache and L2-Cache.

fields.name: LOCK_DONE
fields.desc: The bit is used to indicate whether unlock/lock operation is finished or not. 0: not finished. 1: finished.

fields.name: LOCK_RGID
fields.desc: The bit is used to set  the gid of cache lock/unlock.

fields.name: LOCK_MAP
fields.desc: Those bits are used to indicate which caches in the two-level cache structure will apply this lock/unlock operation. [0]: L1-ICache0, [1]: L1-ICache1, [2]: L1-ICache2, [3]: L1-ICache3, [4]: L1-DCache, [5]: L2-Cache.

fields.name: LOCK_ADDR
fields.desc: Those bits are used to configure the start virtual address of the lock/unlock operation, which should be used together with CACHE_LOCK_SIZE_REG

fields.name: LOCK_SIZE
fields.desc: Those bits are used to configure the size of the lock/unlock operation, which should be used together with CACHE_LOCK_ADDR_REG

fields.name: INVALIDATE_ENA
fields.desc: The bit is used to enable invalidate operation. It will be cleared by hardware after invalidate operation done. Note that this bit and the other sync-bits (clean_ena, writeback_ena, writeback_invalidate_ena) are mutually exclusive, that is, those bits can not be set to 1 at the same time.

fields.name: CLEAN_ENA
fields.desc: The bit is used to enable clean operation. It will be cleared by hardware after clean operation done. Note that this bit and the other sync-bits (invalidate_ena, writeback_ena, writeback_invalidate_ena) are mutually exclusive, that is, those bits can not be set to 1 at the same time.

fields.name: WRITEBACK_ENA
fields.desc: The bit is used to enable writeback operation. It will be cleared by hardware after writeback operation done. Note that this bit and the other sync-bits (invalidate_ena, clean_ena, writeback_invalidate_ena) are mutually exclusive, that is, those bits can not be set to 1 at the same time.

fields.name: WRITEBACK_INVALIDATE_ENA
fields.desc: The bit is used to enable writeback-invalidate operation. It will be cleared by hardware after writeback-invalidate operation done. Note that this bit and the other sync-bits (invalidate_ena, clean_ena, writeback_ena) are mutually exclusive, that is, those bits can not be set to 1 at the same time.

fields.name: SYNC_DONE
fields.desc: The bit is used to indicate whether sync operation (invalidate, clean, writeback, writeback_invalidate) is finished or not. 0: not finished. 1: finished.

fields.name: SYNC_RGID
fields.desc: The bit is used to set  the gid of cache sync operation (invalidate, clean, writeback, writeback_invalidate)

fields.name: SYNC_MAP
fields.desc: Those bits are used to indicate which caches in the two-level cache structure will apply the sync operation. [0]: L1-ICache0, [1]: L1-ICache1, [2]: L1-ICache2, [3]: L1-ICache3, [4]: L1-DCache, [5]: L2-Cache.

fields.name: SYNC_ADDR
fields.desc: Those bits are used to configure the start virtual address of the sync operation, which should be used together with CACHE_SYNC_SIZE_REG

fields.name: SYNC_SIZE
fields.desc: Those bits are used to configure the size of the sync operation, which should be used together with CACHE_SYNC_ADDR_REG

fields.name: L1_ICACHE3_PLD_DONE_INT_ENA

fields.name: SYNC_ERR_INT_CLR

fields.name: L1_ICACHE1_PLD_ERR_INT_RAW

fields.name: L1_ICACHE3_PLD_ERR_INT_RAW

1072759364.desc: L1-Cache Access Fail Interrupt status register

fields.name: L1_ICACHE0_PLD_DONE_INT_ST
fields.desc: The bit indicates the status of the interrupt that occurs only when L1-ICache0 preload-operation is done.

fields.name: L1_ICACHE1_PLD_DONE_INT_ST
fields.desc: The bit indicates the status of the interrupt that occurs only when L1-ICache1 preload-operation is done.

fields.name: L1_ICACHE2_PLD_DONE_INT_ST
fields.desc: Reserved

fields.name: L1_ICACHE3_PLD_DONE_INT_ST
fields.desc: Reserved

fields.name: L1_DCACHE_PLD_DONE_INT_ST
fields.desc: The bit indicates the status of the interrupt that occurs only when L1-DCache preload-operation is done.

fields.name: SYNC_DONE_INT_ST
fields.desc: The bit indicates the status of the interrupt that occurs only when Cache sync-operation is done.

fields.name: L1_ICACHE0_PLD_ERR_INT_ST
fields.desc: The bit indicates the status of the interrupt of L1-ICache0 preload-operation error.

fields.name: L1_ICACHE1_PLD_ERR_INT_ST
fields.desc: The bit indicates the status of the interrupt of L1-ICache1 preload-operation error.

fields.name: L1_ICACHE2_PLD_ERR_INT_ST
fields.desc: Reserved

fields.name: L1_ICACHE3_PLD_ERR_INT_ST
fields.desc: Reserved

fields.name: L1_DCACHE_PLD_ERR_INT_ST
fields.desc: The bit indicates the status of the interrupt of L1-DCache preload-operation error.

fields.name: SYNC_ERR_INT_ST
fields.desc: The bit indicates the status of the interrupt of Cache sync-operation error.

fields.name: L1_ICACHE0_PLD_ERR_CODE
fields.desc: The value 2 is Only available which means preload size is error in L1-ICache0.

fields.name: L1_ICACHE1_PLD_ERR_CODE
fields.desc: The value 2 is Only available which means preload size is error in L1-ICache1.

fields.name: L1_ICACHE2_PLD_ERR_CODE
fields.desc: Reserved

fields.name: L1_ICACHE3_PLD_ERR_CODE
fields.desc: Reserved

fields.name: L1_DCACHE_PLD_ERR_CODE
fields.desc: The value 2 is Only available which means preload size is error in L1-DCache.

fields.name: SYNC_ERR_CODE
fields.desc: The values 0-2 are available which means sync map, command conflict and size are error in Cache System.

fields.name: L1_ICACHE0_SYNC_RST
fields.desc: set this bit to reset sync-logic inside L1-ICache0. Recommend that this should only be used to initialize sync-logic when some fatal error of sync-logic occurs.

fields.name: L1_ICACHE1_SYNC_RST
fields.desc: set this bit to reset sync-logic inside L1-ICache1. Recommend that this should only be used to initialize sync-logic when some fatal error of sync-logic occurs.

fields.name: L1_ICACHE2_SYNC_RST
fields.desc: Reserved

fields.name: L1_ICACHE3_SYNC_RST
fields.desc: Reserved

fields.name: L1_DCACHE_SYNC_RST
fields.desc: set this bit to reset sync-logic inside L1-DCache. Recommend that this should only be used to initialize sync-logic when some fatal error of sync-logic occurs.

fields.name: L1_ICACHE0_PLD_RST
fields.desc: set this bit to reset preload-logic inside L1-ICache0. Recommend that this should only be used to initialize preload-logic when some fatal error of preload-logic occurs.

fields.name: L1_ICACHE1_PLD_RST
fields.desc: set this bit to reset preload-logic inside L1-ICache1. Recommend that this should only be used to initialize preload-logic when some fatal error of preload-logic occurs.

fields.name: L1_ICACHE2_PLD_RST
fields.desc: Reserved

fields.name: L1_ICACHE3_PLD_RST
fields.desc: Reserved

fields.name: L1_DCACHE_PLD_RST
fields.desc: set this bit to reset preload-logic inside L1-DCache. Recommend that this should only be used to initialize preload-logic when some fatal error of preload-logic occurs.

1072759380.name: L1_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_BUF_CLR_CTRL
1072759380.desc: Cache Autoload buffer clear control register

fields.name: L1_ICACHE0_ALD_BUF_CLR
fields.desc: set this bit to clear autoload-buffer inside L1-ICache0. If this bit is active, autoload will not work in L1-ICache0. This bit should not be active when autoload works in L1-ICache0.

fields.name: L1_ICACHE1_ALD_BUF_CLR
fields.desc: set this bit to clear autoload-buffer inside L1-ICache1. If this bit is active, autoload will not work in L1-ICache1. This bit should not be active when autoload works in L1-ICache1.

fields.name: L1_ICACHE2_ALD_BUF_CLR
fields.desc: Reserved

fields.name: L1_ICACHE3_ALD_BUF_CLR
fields.desc: Reserved

fields.name: L1_DCACHE_ALD_BUF_CLR
fields.desc: set this bit to clear autoload-buffer inside L1-DCache. If this bit is active, autoload will not work in L1-DCache. This bit should not be active when autoload works in L1-DCache.

fields.name: L1_ICACHE0_UNALLOC_CLR
fields.desc: The bit is used to clear the unallocate request buffer of l1 icache0 where the unallocate request is responsed but not completed.

fields.name: L1_ICACHE1_UNALLOC_CLR
fields.desc: The bit is used to clear the unallocate request buffer of l1 icache1 where the unallocate request is responsed but not completed.

fields.name: L1_ICACHE2_UNALLOC_CLR
fields.desc: Reserved

fields.name: L1_ICACHE3_UNALLOC_CLR
fields.desc: Reserved

fields.name: L1_DCACHE_UNALLOC_CLR
fields.desc: The bit is used to clear the unallocate request buffer of l1 dcache where the unallocate request is responsed but not completed.

1072759388.desc: Cache Tag and Data memory Object control register

fields.name: L1_ICACHE0_TAG_OBJECT
fields.desc: Set this bit to set L1-ICache0 tag memory as object. This bit should be onehot with the others fields inside this register.

fields.name: L1_ICACHE1_TAG_OBJECT

fields.name: L1_ICACHE2_TAG_OBJECT

fields.name: L1_ICACHE3_TAG_OBJECT

fields.name: L1_DCACHE_TAG_OBJECT

fields.name: L1_ICACHE0_MEM_OBJECT

fields.name: L1_ICACHE1_MEM_OBJECT

fields.name: L1_ICACHE3_MEM_OBJECT
fields.desc: Reserved

fields.name: L1_DCACHE_MEM_OBJECT
fields.desc: Set this bit to set L1-DCache data memory as object. This bit should be onehot with the others fields inside this register.

1072759392.desc: Cache Tag and Data memory way register

fields.name: L1_CACHE_WAY_OBJECT
fields.desc: Set this bits to select which way of the tag-object will be accessed. 0: way0, 1: way1, 2: way2, 3: way3, ?, 7: way7.

fields.name: L1_CACHE_VADDR
fields.desc: Those bits stores the virtual address which will decide where inside the specified tag memory object will be accessed.

fields.name: L1_CACHE_DEBUG_BUS
fields.desc: This is a constant place where we can write data to or read data from the tag/data memory on the specified cache.

1072759404.name: LEVEL_SPLIT0
1072759404.desc: USED TO SPLIT L1 CACHE AND L2 CACHE

fields.name: LEVEL_SPLIT0
fields.desc: Reserved

fields.name: L2_CACHE_SHUT_DMA
fields.desc: The bit is used to disable DMA access L2-Cache, 0: enable, 1: disable

fields.name: L2_CACHE_UNDEF_OP
fields.desc: Reserved

fields.name: BYPASS_L2_CACHE_EN
fields.desc: The bit is used to enable bypass L2-Cache. 0: disable bypass, 1: enable bypass.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_CACHESIZE_512

fields.name: L2_CACHE_CACHESIZE_64K

fields.name: L2_CACHE_CACHESIZE_128K

fields.name: L2_CACHE_CACHESIZE_256K
fields.desc: The field is used to configure cachesize of L2-Cache as 256k bytes. This field and all other fields within this register is onehot.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_CACHESIZE_512K
fields.desc: The field is used to configure cachesize of L2-Cache as 512k bytes. This field and all other fields within this register is onehot.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_CACHESIZE_1024K
fields.desc: The field is used to configure cachesize of L2-Cache as 1024k bytes. This field and all other fields within this register is onehot.

1072759420.name: L2_CACHE_BLOCKSIZE_CONF
1072759420.desc: L2 Cache BlockSize mode configure register

fields.name: L2_CACHE_BLOCKSIZE_8
fields.desc: The field is used to configureblocksize of L2-Cache as 8 bytes. This field and all other fields within this register is onehot.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_BLOCKSIZE_16
fields.desc: The field is used to configureblocksize of L2-Cache as 16 bytes. This field and all other fields within this register is onehot.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_BLOCKSIZE_32

fields.name: L2_CACHE_BLOCKSIZE_128
fields.desc: The field is used to configureblocksize of L2-Cache as 128 bytes. This field and all other fields within this register is onehot.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_BLOCKSIZE_256
fields.desc: The field is used to configureblocksize of L2-Cache as 256 bytes. This field and all other fields within this register is onehot.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_WRAP
fields.desc: Set this bit as 1 to enable L2-Cache wrap around mode.

1072759428.name: L2_CACHE_TAG_MEM_POWER_CTRL
1072759428.desc: Cache tag memory power control register

fields.name: L2_CACHE_TAG_MEM_FORCE_ON
fields.desc: The bit is used to close clock gating of  L2-Cache tag memory. 1: close gating, 0: open clock gating.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_TAG_MEM_FORCE_PD
fields.desc: The bit is used to power L2-Cache tag memory down. 0: follow rtc_lslp, 1: power down

fields.name: L2_CACHE_TAG_MEM_FORCE_PU
fields.desc: The bit is used to power L2-Cache tag memory up. 0: follow rtc_lslp, 1: power up

1072759432.name: L2_CACHE_DATA_MEM_POWER_CTRL
1072759432.desc: Cache data memory power control register

fields.name: L2_CACHE_DATA_MEM_FORCE_ON
fields.desc: The bit is used to close clock gating of  L2-Cache data memory. 1: close gating, 0: open clock gating.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_DATA_MEM_FORCE_PD
fields.desc: The bit is used to power L2-Cache data memory down. 0: follow rtc_lslp, 1: power down

fields.name: L2_CACHE_DATA_MEM_FORCE_PU
fields.desc: The bit is used to power L2-Cache data memory up. 0: follow rtc_lslp, 1: power up

fields.name: L2_CACHE_FREEZE_EN
fields.desc: The bit is used to enable freeze operation on L2-Cache. It can be cleared by software.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_FREEZE_MODE
fields.desc: The bit is used to configure mode of freeze operation L2-Cache. 0: a miss-access will not stuck. 1: a miss-access will stuck.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_FREEZE_DONE
fields.desc: The bit is used to indicate whether freeze operation on L2-Cache is finished or not. 0: not finished. 1: finished.

1072759440.name: L2_CACHE_DATA_MEM_ACS_CONF
1072759440.desc: Cache data memory access configure register

fields.name: L2_CACHE_DATA_MEM_RD_EN
fields.desc: The bit is used to enable config-bus read L2-Cache data memoryory. 0: disable, 1: enable.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_DATA_MEM_WR_EN
fields.desc: The bit is used to enable config-bus write L2-Cache data memoryory. 0: disable, 1: enable.

1072759444.name: L2_CACHE_TAG_MEM_ACS_CONF
1072759444.desc: Cache tag memory access configure register

fields.name: L2_CACHE_TAG_MEM_RD_EN
fields.desc: The bit is used to enable config-bus read L2-Cache tag memoryory. 0: disable, 1: enable.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_TAG_MEM_WR_EN
fields.desc: The bit is used to enable config-bus write L2-Cache tag memoryory. 0: disable, 1: enable.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_PRELOCK_SCT0_EN
fields.desc: The bit is used to enable the first section of prelock function on L2-Cache.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_PRELOCK_SCT1_EN
fields.desc: The bit is used to enable the second section of prelock function on L2-Cache.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_PRELOCK_RGID
fields.desc: The bit is used to set  the gid of l2 cache prelock.

1072759452.name: L2_CACHE_PRELOCK_SCT0_ADDR
1072759452.desc: L2 Cache prelock section0 address configure register

fields.name: L2_CACHE_PRELOCK_SCT0_ADDR
fields.desc: Those bits are used to configure the start virtual address of the first section of prelock on L2-Cache, which should be used together with L2_CACHE_PRELOCK_SCT0_SIZE_REG

1072759456.name: L2_CACHE_PRELOCK_SCT1_ADDR
1072759456.desc: L2 Cache prelock section1 address configure register

fields.name: L2_CACHE_PRELOCK_SCT1_ADDR
fields.desc: Those bits are used to configure the start virtual address of the second section of prelock on L2-Cache, which should be used together with L2_CACHE_PRELOCK_SCT1_SIZE_REG

1072759460.name: L2_CACHE_PRELOCK_SCT_SIZE
1072759460.desc: L2 Cache prelock section size configure register

fields.name: L2_CACHE_PRELOCK_SCT0_SIZE
fields.desc: Those bits are used to configure the size of the first section of prelock on L2-Cache, which should be used together with L2_CACHE_PRELOCK_SCT0_ADDR_REG

fields.name: L2_CACHE_PRELOCK_SCT1_SIZE
fields.desc: Those bits are used to configure the size of the second section of prelock on L2-Cache, which should be used together with L2_CACHE_PRELOCK_SCT1_ADDR_REG

fields.name: L2_CACHE_PRELOAD_ENA
fields.desc: The bit is used to enable preload operation on L2-Cache. It will be cleared by hardware automatically after preload operation is done.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_PRELOAD_DONE
fields.desc: The bit is used to indicate whether preload operation is finished or not. 0: not finished. 1: finished.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_PRELOAD_ORDER
fields.desc: The bit is used to configure the direction of preload operation. 0: ascending, 1: descending.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_PRELOAD_RGID
fields.desc: The bit is used to set  the gid of l2 cache preload.

1072759468.name: L2_CACHE_PRELOAD_ADDR
1072759468.desc: L2 Cache preload address configure register

fields.name: L2_CACHE_PRELOAD_ADDR
fields.desc: Those bits are used to configure the start virtual address of preload on L2-Cache, which should be used together with L2_CACHE_PRELOAD_SIZE_REG

1072759472.name: L2_CACHE_PRELOAD_SIZE
1072759472.desc: L2 Cache preload size configure register

fields.name: L2_CACHE_PRELOAD_SIZE
fields.desc: Those bits are used to configure the size of the first section of prelock on L2-Cache, which should be used together with L2_CACHE_PRELOAD_ADDR_REG

fields.name: L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_ENA
fields.desc: The bit is used to enable and disable autoload operation on L2-Cache.  1: enable, 0: disable.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_DONE
fields.desc: The bit is used to indicate whether autoload operation on L2-Cache is finished or not. 0: not finished. 1: finished.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_ORDER
fields.desc: The bit is used to configure the direction of autoload operation on L2-Cache. 0: ascending. 1: descending.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_AUTOLOAD_TRIGGER_MODE

fields.desc: The bit indicates the status of the interrupt of L2-Cache preload-operation error.

fields.desc: The value 2 is Only available which means preload size is error in L2-Cache.

fields.desc: set this bit to reset sync-logic inside L2-Cache. Recommend that this should only be used to initialize sync-logic when some fatal error of sync-logic occurs.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_PLD_RST
fields.desc: set this bit to reset preload-logic inside L2-Cache. Recommend that this should only be used to initialize preload-logic when some fatal error of preload-logic occurs.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_ALD_BUF_CLR
fields.desc: set this bit to clear autoload-buffer inside L2-Cache. If this bit is active, autoload will not work in L2-Cache. This bit should not be active when autoload works in L2-Cache.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_UNALLOC_CLR
fields.desc: The bit is used to clear the unallocate request buffer of l2 icache where the unallocate request is responsed but not completed.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_ACCESS_FORCE_CC
fields.desc: Set this bit to force the request to l2 cache with cacheable attribute, otherwise, the attribute is propagated from L1 cache or CPU, it could be one of cacheable and non-cacheable.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_ACCESS_FORCE_WB
fields.desc: Set this bit to force the request to l2 cache with write-back attribute, otherwise, the attribute is propagated from L1 cache or CPU, it could be one of write-back and write-through.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_ACCESS_FORCE_WMA
fields.desc: Set this bit to force the request to l2 cache with write-miss-allocate attribute, otherwise, the attribute is propagated from L1 cache or CPU, it could be one of write-miss-allocate and write-miss-no-allocate.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_ACCESS_FORCE_RMA
fields.desc: Set this bit to force the request to l2 cache with read-miss-allocate attribute, otherwise, the attribute is propagated from L1 cache or CPU, it could be one of read-miss-allocate and read-miss-no-allocate.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_TAG_OBJECT
fields.desc: Set this bit to set L2-Cache tag memory as object. This bit should be onehot with the others fields inside this register.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_MEM_OBJECT
fields.desc: Set this bit to set L2-Cache data memory as object. This bit should be onehot with the others fields inside this register.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_WAY_OBJECT
fields.desc: Set this bits to select which way of the tag-object will be accessed. 0: way0, 1: way1, 2: way2, 3: way3, ?, 7: way7.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_VADDR
fields.desc: Those bits stores the virtual address which will decide where inside the specified tag memory object will be accessed.

fields.name: L2_CACHE_DEBUG_BUS
fields.desc: This is a constant place where we can write data to or read data from the tag/data memory on the specified cache.

fields.name: CLK_EN
fields.desc: 0: enable clock gating. 1: disable clock gating, clock always on.

fields.name: CSI_BRIG_EN
fields.desc: 0: disable csi bridge. 1: enable csi bridge.

fields.name: DMA_BURST_LEN
fields.desc: DMA burst length.

fields.desc: 1: reg_dma_burst_len & reg_dma_burst_len will be updated by dma block finish. 0: updated by frame.

fields.name: DMA_FORCE_RD_STATUS
fields.desc: 1: mask dma request when reading frame info. 0: disable mask.

fields.desc: buffer almost full threshold.

fields.desc: buffer data count.

fields.name: SET_START
fields.desc: set this bit to start DS operation.

fields.name: SET_CONTINUE
fields.desc: set this bit to continue DS operation.

fields.name: SET_FINISH
fields.desc: Set this bit to finish DS process.

fields.name: QUERY_BUSY
fields.desc: digital signature state. 1'b0: idle, 1'b1: busy

fields.name: QUERY_KEY_WRONG
fields.desc: digital signature key wrong counter

fields.name: MD_ERROR
fields.desc: MD checkout result. 1'b0: MD check pass, 1'b1: MD check fail

fields.name: PADDING_BAD
fields.desc: padding checkout result. 1'b0: a good padding, 1'b1: a bad padding

fields.name: DATE
fields.desc: ds version information

fields.name: CLK_EN
fields.desc: this bit configures force_on of dsi_bridge register clock gate

fields.name: DSI_EN
fields.desc: this bit configures module enable of dsi_bridge. 0: disable, 1: enable

1342834696.name: DMA_REQ_CFG
1342834696.desc: dsi bridge dma burst len register

fields.name: DMA_BURST_LEN
fields.desc: this field configures the num of 64-bit in one dma burst transfer, valid only when dsi_bridge as flow controller

1342834700.name: RAW_NUM_CFG
1342834700.desc: dsi bridge raw number control register

fields.name: RAW_NUM_TOTAL
fields.desc: this field configures number of total pix bits/64

fields.name: UNALIGN_64BIT_EN
fields.desc: this field configures whether the total pix bits is a multiple of 64bits. 0: align to 64-bit, 1: unalign to 64-bit

fields.name: RAW_NUM_TOTAL_SET
fields.desc: this bit configures enable of reload reg_raw_num_total to internal cnt. 0: disable, 1: enable. valid only when dsi_bridge as flow controller

fields.name: CREDIT_THRD
fields.desc: this field configures the threshold whether dsi_bridge fifo can receive one more 64-bit, valid only when dsi_bridge as flow controller

fields.name: CREDIT_BURST_THRD
fields.desc: this field configures the threshold whether dsi_bridge fifo can receive one more dma burst, valid only when dsi_bridge as flow controller

fields.name: CREDIT_RESET
fields.desc: this bit configures internal credit cnt clear, 0: non, 1: reset. valid only when dsi_bridge as flow controller

fields.name: CALC_DONE_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw interrupt status bit  for the ecc_calc_done_int interrupt

fields.desc: The masked interrupt status bit  for the ecc_calc_done_int interrupt

fields.name: CALC_DONE_INT_ENA
fields.desc: The interrupt enable bit  for the ecc_calc_done_int interrupt

fields.name: CALC_DONE_INT_CLR
fields.desc: Set this bit to clear the ecc_calc_done_int interrupt

fields.name: START
fields.desc: Write 1 to start caculation of ECC Accelerator. This bit will be self-cleared after the caculatrion is done.

fields.name: RESET
fields.desc: Write 1 to reset ECC Accelerator.

fields.name: KEY_LENGTH
fields.desc: The key length mode bit of ECC Accelerator.  0: P-192.  1: P-256.

fields.name: MOD_BASE
fields.desc: The mod base of mod operation, only valid in work_mode 8-11. 0: n(order of curve). 1: p(mod base of curve)

fields.name: WORK_MODE
fields.desc: The work mode bits of ECC Accelerator. 0: Point Mult Mode. 1: Reserved. 2: Point verification mode. 3: Point Verif+mult mode. 4: Jacobian Point Mult Mode. 5: Point Add Mode. 6: Jacobian Point Verification Mode. 7: Point Verif + Jacobian Mult Mode. 8: mod addition. 9. mod substraction. 10: mod multiplication. 11: mod division.

fields.name: SECURITY_MODE
fields.desc: Reserved

fields.name: VERIFICATION_RESULT
fields.desc: The verification result bit of ECC Accelerator, only valid when calculation is done.

fields.name: CLK_EN
fields.desc: Write 1 to force on register clock gate.

fields.name: MEM_CLOCK_GATE_FORCE_ON
fields.desc: ECC memory clock gate force on register

fields.name: DATE
fields.desc: ECC mult version control register

fields.name: WORK_MODE
fields.desc: The work mode bits of ECDSA Accelerator. 0: Signature Verify Mode. 1: Signature Generate Mode. 2: Export Public Key Mode. 3: invalid.

fields.name: ECC_CURVE
fields.desc: The ecc curve select bit of ECDSA Accelerator.  0: P-192.  1: P-256.

fields.name: SOFTWARE_SET_K
fields.desc: The source of k select bit. 0: k is automatically generated by hardware. 1: k is written by software.

fields.name: SOFTWARE_SET_Z
fields.desc: The source of z select bit. 0: z is generated from SHA result. 1: z is written by software.

fields.name: DETERMINISTIC_K
fields.desc: The source of hardware generated k. 0: k is generated by TRNG. 1: k is generated by deterministic derivation algorithm.

fields.name: DETERMINISTIC_LOOP
fields.desc: The (loop number - 1) value in the deterministic derivation algorithm to derive k.

fields.name: GATE_FORCE_ON
fields.desc: Write 1 to force on register clock gate.

fields.name: START
fields.desc: Write 1 to start caculation of ECDSA Accelerator. This bit will be self-cleared after configuration.

fields.name: LOAD_DONE
fields.desc: Write 1 to input load done signal of ECDSA Accelerator. This bit will be self-cleared after configuration.

fields.name: GET_DONE
fields.desc: Write 1 to input get done signal of ECDSA Accelerator. This bit will be self-cleared after configuration.

fields.name: BUSY
fields.desc: The status bits of ECDSA Accelerator. ECDSA is at 0: IDLE, 1: LOAD, 2: GET, 3: BUSY state.

fields.name: OPERATION_RESULT
fields.desc: The operation result bit of ECDSA Accelerator, only valid when ECDSA calculation is done.

fields.name: K_VALUE_WARNING
fields.desc: The k value warning bit of ECDSA Accelerator, valid when k value is bigger than the curve order, then actually taken k = k mod n.

fields.name: DATE
fields.desc: ECDSA version control register

fields.name: SHA_MODE
fields.desc: The work mode bits of SHA Calculator in ECDSA Accelerator. 1: SHA-224. 2: SHA-256. Others: invalid.

fields.name: SHA_START
fields.desc: Write 1 to start the first caculation of SHA Calculator in ECDSA Accelerator. This bit will be self-cleared after configuration.

fields.name: SHA_CONTINUE
fields.desc: Write 1 to start the latter caculation of SHA Calculator in ECDSA Accelerator. This bit will be self-cleared after configuration.

fields.name: SHA_BUSY
fields.desc: The busy status bit of SHA Calculator in ECDSA Accelerator. 1:SHA is in calculation. 0: SHA is idle.

fields.name: FRAME_START
fields.desc: Configures whether or not to start encoding one frame.\\0: Invalid. No effect\\1: Start encoding one frame

fields.desc: Configures whether or not to start moving reference data from external mem.\\0: Invalid. No effect\\1: H264 start moving two MB lines of reference frame from external mem to internal mem

fields.name: FRAME_MODE
fields.desc: Configures H264 running mode. When field H264_DUAL_STREAM_MODE is set to 1, this field must be set to 1 too.\\0: GOP mode. Before every GOP first frame start, need reconfig reference frame DMA\\1: Frame mode. Before every frame start, need reconfig reference frame DMA

fields.name: SYS_RST_PULSE
fields.desc: Configures whether or not to reset H264 ip.\\0: Invalid. No effect\\1: Reset H264 ip

fields.name: DUAL_STREAM_MODE
fields.desc: Configures whether or not to enable dual stream mode. When this field is set to 1,  H264_FRAME_MODE field must be set to 1 too.\\0: Normal mode\\1: Dual stream mode

fields.name: GOP_NUM
fields.desc: Configures the frame number of one GOP.\\0: The frame number of one GOP is infinite\\Others: Actual frame number of one GOP

fields.name: IN_ECC_AES_EN_CH0

fields.name: IN_CHECK_OWNER_CH0
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable checking the owner attribute of the link descriptor.

fields.name: IN_MEM_BURST_LENGTH_CH0
fields.desc: Block size of Rx channel 0. 0: single      1: 16 bytes      2: 32 bytes    3: 64 bytes    4: 128 bytes

fields.name: IN_PAGE_BOUND_EN_CH0
fields.desc: Set this bit to 1 to make sure AXI write data don't cross the address boundary which define by mem_burst_length

fields.name: IN_RST_CH0
fields.desc: Write 1 then write 0 to this bit to reset Rx channel

fields.name: IN_CMD_DISABLE_CH0
fields.desc: Write 1 before reset and write 0 after reset

fields.name: IN_ARB_WEIGHT_OPT_DIS_CH0
fields.desc: Set this bit to 1 to disable arbiter optimum weight function.

fields.name: IN_SUC_EOF_CH0_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when the last data pointed by one inlink descriptor has been received and no data error is detected for Rx channel 0.

fields.name: IN_ERR_EOF_CH0_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when the last data pointed by one inlink descriptor has been received and data error is detected

fields.name: IN_DSCR_ERR_CH0_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when detecting inlink descriptor error, including owner error, the second and third word error of inlink descriptor for Rx channel 0.

fields.name: INFIFO_OVF_L1_CH0_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when fifo of Rx channel is overflow.

fields.name: INFIFO_UDF_L1_CH0_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when fifo of Rx channel is underflow.

fields.name: INFIFO_OVF_L2_CH0_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when fifo of Rx channel is overflow.

fields.name: INFIFO_UDF_L2_CH0_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when fifo of Rx channel is underflow.

fields.name: IN_DSCR_EMPTY_CH0_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when the last descriptor is done but fifo also remain data.

fields.name: IN_DSCR_TASK_OVF_CH0_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when dscr ready task fifo is overflow.

fields.name: MODE
fields.desc: Set this field to choose the huk process. 1: process huk generate mode. 0: process huk recovery mode.

fields.name: START
fields.desc: Write 1 to continue HUK Generator operation at LOAD/GAIN state.

fields.name: CONTINUE
fields.desc: Write 1 to start HUK Generator at IDLE state.

fields.name: STATE
fields.desc: The state of HUK Generator. 0: IDLE. 1: LOAD. 2: GAIN. 3: BUSY.

fields.name: STATUS
fields.desc: The HUK generation status. 0: HUK is not generated. 1: HUK is generated and valid. 2: HUK is generated but invalid. 3: reserved.

fields.name: RISK_LEVEL
fields.desc: The risk level of HUK. 0-6: the higher the risk level is, the more error bits there are in the PUF SRAM. 7: Error Level, HUK is invalid.

fields.name: DATE
fields.desc: HUK Generator version control register.

1343308032.name: INFO_MEM[%s]
1343308032.desc: The memory that stores HUK info.

1342980096.name: SCL_LOW_PERIOD
1342980096.desc: Configures the low level width of the SCL Clock.

fields.name: SCL_LOW_PERIOD
fields.desc:
Configures the low level width of the SCL Clock. 
Measurement unit: i2c_sclk.

fields.name: SDA_FORCE_OUT
fields.desc:
Configures the SDA output mode
1: Direct output,

0: Open drain output.

fields.name: SCL_FORCE_OUT
fields.desc:
Configures the SCL output mode
1: Direct output,

0: Open drain output.

fields.name: SAMPLE_SCL_LEVEL
fields.desc:
Configures the sample mode for SDA.
1: Sample SDA data on the SCL low level.

0: Sample SDA data on the SCL high level.

fields.name: RX_FULL_ACK_LEVEL
fields.desc: Configures the ACK value that needs to be sent by master when the rx_fifo_cnt has reached the threshold.

fields.name: MS_MODE
fields.desc:
Configures the module as an I2C Master or Slave. 
0: Slave

1: Master

fields.name: TRANS_START
fields.desc:
Configures to start sending the data in txfifo for slave. 
0: No effect

1: Start

fields.name: TX_LSB_FIRST
fields.desc:
Configures to control the sending order for data needing to be sent. 
1: send data from the least significant bit,

0: send data from the most significant bit.

fields.name: RX_LSB_FIRST
fields.desc:
Configures to control the storage order for received data.
1: receive data from the least significant bit

0: receive data from the most significant bit.

fields.name: CLK_EN
fields.desc:
Configures whether to gate clock signal for registers.

0: Force clock on for registers 

1: Support clock only when registers are read or written to by software.

fields.name: ARBITRATION_EN
fields.desc:
Configures to enable I2C bus arbitration detection.
0: No effect

1: Enable

fields.name: FSM_RST
fields.desc:
Configures to reset the SCL_FSM.
0: No effect

1: Reset

fields.name: CONF_UPGATE
fields.desc:
Configures this bit for synchronization
0: No effect

1: Synchronize

fields.name: SLV_TX_AUTO_START_EN
fields.desc:
Configures to enable slave to send data automatically
0: Disable

1: Enable

fields.name: ADDR_10BIT_RW_CHECK_EN
fields.desc:
Configures to check if the r/w bit of 10bit addressing consists with I2C protocol.
0: Not check

1: Check

fields.name: ADDR_BROADCASTING_EN
fields.desc:
Configures to support the 7bit general call function. 
0: Not support

1: Support

fields.name: RESP_REC
fields.desc:
Represents the received ACK value in master mode or slave mode.
0: ACK,

1: NACK.

fields.name: SLAVE_RW
fields.desc:
Represents the transfer direction in slave mode,.
1: Master reads from slave,

0: Master writes to slave.

fields.name: ARB_LOST
fields.desc:
Represents whether the I2C controller loses control of SCL line.
0: No arbitration lost

1: Arbitration lost

fields.name: BUS_BUSY
fields.desc:
Represents the I2C bus state.
1: The I2C bus is busy transferring data, 

0: The I2C bus is in idle state.

fields.name: SLAVE_ADDRESSED
fields.desc:
Represents whether the address sent by the master is equal to the address of the slave.
Valid only when the module is configured as an I2C Slave.
0: Not equal

1: Equal

fields.name: RXFIFO_CNT
fields.desc: Represents the number of data bytes to be sent.

fields.name: STRETCH_CAUSE
fields.desc:
Represents the cause of SCL clocking stretching in slave mode.
0: Stretching SCL low when the master starts to read data.

1: Stretching SCL low when I2C TX FIFO is empty in slave mode.

2: Stretching SCL low when I2C RX FIFO is full in slave mode.

fields.name: TXFIFO_CNT
fields.desc: Represents the number of data bytes received in RAM.

fields.name: SCL_MAIN_STATE_LAST
fields.desc:
Represents the states of the I2C module state machine. 
0: Idle,

1: Address shift,

2: ACK address,

3: Rx data,

4: Tx data,

5: Send ACK,

6: Wait ACK

fields.name: SCL_STATE_LAST
fields.desc:
Represents the states of the state machine used to produce SCL.
0: Idle,

1: Start,

2: Negative edge,

3: Low,

4: Positive edge,

5: High,

6: Stop

1342980108.name: TO
1342980108.desc: Setting time out control for receiving data.

fields.name: TIME_OUT_VALUE
fields.desc:
Configures the timeout threshold period for SCL stucking at high or low level. The actual period is 2^(reg_time_out_value).
Measurement unit: i2c_sclk.

fields.name: TIME_OUT_EN
fields.desc:
Configures to enable time out control.
0: No effect

1: Enable

fields.name: SLAVE_ADDR
fields.desc: Configure the slave address of I2C Slave.

fields.name: ADDR_10BIT_EN
fields.desc:
Configures to enable the slave 10-bit addressing mode in master mode. 
0: No effect

1: Enable

fields.name: RXFIFO_RADDR
fields.desc: Represents the offset address of the APB reading from RXFIFO

fields.name: RXFIFO_WADDR
fields.desc: Represents the offset address of i2c module receiving data and writing to RXFIFO.

fields.name: TXFIFO_RADDR
fields.desc: Represents the offset address of i2c module reading from TXFIFO.

fields.name: TXFIFO_WADDR
fields.desc: Represents the offset address of APB bus writing to TXFIFO.

fields.name: SLAVE_RW_POINT
fields.desc: Represents the offset address in the I2C Slave RAM addressed by I2C Master when in I2C slave mode.

fields.name: RXFIFO_WM_THRHD
fields.desc: Configures the water mark threshold of RXFIFO in nonfifo access mode. When reg_reg_fifo_prt_en is 1 and rx FIFO counter is bigger than reg_rxfifo_wm_thrhd[4:0], reg_rxfifo_wm_int_raw bit will be valid.

fields.name: TXFIFO_WM_THRHD
fields.desc: Configures the water mark threshold of TXFIFO in nonfifo access mode. When reg_reg_fifo_prt_en is 1 and tx FIFO counter is smaller than reg_txfifo_wm_thrhd[4:0], reg_txfifo_wm_int_raw bit will be valid.

fields.name: NONFIFO_EN
fields.desc: Configures to enable APB nonfifo access.

fields.name: FIFO_ADDR_CFG_EN
fields.desc:
Configures to enable double addressing mode. When this mode is enabled, the byte received after the I2C address byte represents the offset address in the I2C Slave RAM. 
0: Disable

1: Enable

fields.name: RX_FIFO_RST
fields.desc:
Configures to reset RXFIFO.
0: No effect

1: Reset

fields.name: TX_FIFO_RST
fields.desc:
Configures to reset TXFIFO.
0: No effect

1: Reset

fields.name: FIFO_PRT_EN
fields.desc:
Configures to enable FIFO pointer in non-fifo access mode. This bit controls the valid bits and the TX/RX FIFO overflow, underflow, full and empty interrupts.
0: No effect

1: Enable

fields.name: FIFO_RDATA

fields.name: COMMAND0
fields.desc:
Configures command 0. It consists of three parts: 
op_code is the command,
0: RSTART, 
1: WRITE,
2: READ,
3: STOP,
4: END.

Byte_num represents the number of bytes that need to be sent or received.
ack_check_en, ack_exp and ack are used to control the ACK bit. See I2C cmd structure for more information.

fields.desc:
Configures to enable slave SCL stretch function.

1: Enable
The SCL output line will be stretched low when reg_slave_scl_stretch_en is 1 and stretch event happens. The stretch cause can be seen in reg_stretch_cause.

1343070236.name: BUFFER_THLD_CTRL
1343070236.desc: In-Band Interrupt Status Threshold Value . Every In Band Interrupt received by I3C controller generates an IBI status. This field controls the number of IBI status entries in the IBI buffer that trigger the IBI_STATUS_THLD_STAT interrupt.

fields.name: REG_CMD_BUF_EMPTY_THLD
fields.desc: Command Buffer Empty Threshold Value is used to control the number of empty locations(or greater) in the Command Buffer that trigger CMD_BUFFER_READY_STAT interrupt.

fields.name: REG_RESP_BUF_THLD
fields.desc: Response Buffer Threshold Value is used to control the number of entries in the Response Buffer that trigger the RESP_READY_STAT_INTR.

fields.name: REG_IBI_DATA_BUF_THLD
fields.desc: In-Band Interrupt Data Threshold Value . Every In Band Interrupt received by I3C controller generates an IBI status. This field controls the number of IBI data entries in the IBI buffer that trigger the IBI_DATA_THLD_STAT interrupt.

fields.name: REG_IBI_STATUS_BUF_THLD
fields.desc: NA

fields.name: REG_TX_DATA_BUF_THLD
fields.desc: Transmit Buffer Threshold Value. This field controls the number of empty locations in the Transmit FIFO that trigger the TX_THLD_STAT interrupt. Supports values: 000:2  001:4  010:8  011:16  100:31, else:31

fields.name: REG_RX_DATA_BUF_THLD
fields.desc: Receive Buffer Threshold Value. This field controls the number of empty locations in the Receive FIFO that trigger the RX_THLD_STAT interrupt. Supports: 000:2  001:4  010:8  011:16  100:31, else:31

fields.name: REG_NOTIFY_SIR_REJECTED
fields.desc: Notify Rejected Slave Interrupt Request Control. This bit is used to suppress reporting to the application about Slave Interrupt Request. 0:Suppress passing the IBI Status to the IBI FIFO(hence not notifying the application) when a SIR request is NACKed and auto-disabled base on the IBI_SIR_REQ_REJECT register. 1: Writes IBI Status to the IBI FIFO(hence notifying the application) when SIR request is NACKed and auto-disabled based on the IBI_SIR_REQ_REJECT registerl.

fields.name: REG_SIR_REQ_PAYLOAD
fields.desc: NA

fields.name: REG_SIR_REQ_REJECT
fields.desc: The application of controller can decide whether to send ACK or NACK for Slave request received from any I3C device. A device specific response control bit is provided to select the response option, Master will ACK/NACK the Master Request based on programming of control bit, corresponding to the interrupting device. 0:ACK the SIR Request  1:NACK and send direct auto disable CCC

fields.desc: This interrupt is generated when number of entries in receive buffer is greater than or equal to threshold value specified by RX_BUF_THLD field in DATA_BUFFER_THLD_CTRL register. fields.name: RESP_READY_INT_ST
fields.desc: This interrupt is generated when number of entries in response buffer is greater than or equal to threshold value specified by RESP_BUF_THLD field in BUFFER_THLD_CTRL register. fields.desc: Contains a Command Descriptor structure that depends on the requested transfer type. Command Descriptor structure is used to schedule the transfers to devices on I3C bus.

fields.name: RESPONSE
fields.desc: The Response Buffer can be read through this register. The response status for each Command is written into the Response Buffer by the controller if ROC (Response On Completion) bit is set or if transfer error has occurred. The response buffer can be read through this register.

fields.name: RX_DATA_PORT
fields.desc: Receive Data Port. Receive data is mapped to the Rx-data buffer and receive data is always packed in 4-byte aligned data words.  If the length of data transfer is not aligned to 4-bytes boundary, then there will be extra(unused) bytes(the additional data bytes have to be ignored) at the end of the transferred data. The valid data must be identified using the DATA_LENGTH filed in the Response Descriptor.

fields.name: REG_TX_DATA_PORT
fields.desc: Transmit Data Port. Transmit data is mapped to the Tx-data  buffer and transmit data is always packed in 4-byte aligned data words.  If the length of data transfer is not aligned to 4-bytes boundary, then there will be extra(unused) bytes(the additional data bytes have to be ignored) at the end of the transferred data. The valid data must be identified using the DATA_LENGTH filed in the Response Descriptor.

1343070232.name: IBI_STATUS_BUF
1343070232.desc: In-Band Interrupt Buffer Status/Data Register. When receiving an IBI, IBI_PORT is used to both: Read the IBI Status Read the IBI Data(which is raw/opaque data)

fields.name: DATA_LENGTH
fields.desc: This field represents the length of data received along with IBI, in bytes.

fields.name: IBI_ID
fields.desc: IBI Identifier. The byte received after START which includes the address the R/W bit: Device  address and R/W bit in case of Slave Interrupt or Master Request.

fields.name: IBI_STS
fields.desc: IBI received data/status. IBI Data register is mapped to the IBI Buffer. The IBI Data is always packed in4-byte aligned and put to the IBI Buffer. This register When read from, reads the data from the IBI buffer. IBI Status register when read from, returns the data from the IBI Buffer and indicates how the controller responded to incoming IBI(SIR, MR and HJ).

fields.name: REG_DAT_DEV1_NACK_RETRY_CNT
fields.desc: This field is used to set the Device NACK Retry count for the particular device. If the Device NACK's for the device address, the controller automatically retries the same device until this count expires. If the Slave does not ACK for the mentioned number of retries, then controller generates an error response and move to the Halt state.

fields.name: SLVENA
fields.desc: 1: allow the slave to operate on i2c or i3c bus. 0: the slave will ignore the bus. This should be not set until registers such as PARTNO, IDEXT and the like are set 1st  -if used- since they impact data to the master

fields.name: NACK
fields.desc: 1:the slave will NACK all requests to it except CCC broadcast. This should be used with caution as the Master may determine the slave is missing if overused.

fields.name: MATCHSS
fields.desc: 1: the START and STOP sticky STATUS bits will only be set if MATCHED is set..This allows START and STOP to be used to detect end of a message to /from this slave.

fields.name: S0IGNORE
fields.desc: If 1, the Slave will not detect S0 or S1 errors and so not lock up waiting on an Exit Pattern. This should only be used when the bus will not use HDR.

fields.name: DDROK
fields.desc: NA

fields.name: IDRAND
fields.desc: NA

fields.name: OFFLINE
fields.desc: NA

fields.name: BAMATCH
fields.desc: Bus Available condition match value for current ???Slow clock???. This provides the count of the slow clock to count out 1us (or more) to allow an IBI to drive SDA Low when the Master is not doing so. The max width , and so max value, is controlled by the block. Only if enabled for events such IBI or MR or HJ, and if enabled to provide this as a register. With is limited to CLK_SLOW_BITS

fields.name: SADDR
fields.desc: If allowed by the block:sets i2c 7 bits static address,else should be 0. If enabled to use one and to be provided by SW. Block may provide in HW as well.

fields.name: STNOTSTOP
fields.desc: Is 1 if bus is busy(activity) and 0 when in a STOP condition. Other bits may also set when busy. Note that this can also be true from an S0 or S1 error, which waits for an Exit Pattern.

fields.name: STMSG
fields.desc: Is 1 if this bus Slave is listening to the bus traffic or repsonding, If STNOSTOP=1, then this will be 0 when a non-matching address seen until next respeated START it STOP.

fields.name: STCCCH
fields.desc: Is 1 if a CCC message is being handled automatically.

fields.name: STREQRD
fields.desc: 1 if the req in process is an sdr read from this slave or an IBI is being pushed out,

fields.name: STREQWR
fields.desc: NA

fields.name: STDAA
fields.desc: NA

fields.name: STHDR
fields.desc: NA

fields.name: START
fields.desc: NA

fields.name: MATCHED
fields.desc: NA

fields.name: STOP
fields.desc: NA

fields.name: RXPEND
fields.desc: Receiving a message from master,which is not being handled by block(not a CCC internally processed). For all but External FIFO, this uses DATACTRL RXTRIG, which defaults to not-empty. If DMA is enabled for RX, DMA will be signaled as well. Will self-clear if data is read(FIFO and non-FIFO)

fields.name: TXNOTFULL
fields.desc: Is 1 when the To-bus buffer/FIFO can accept more data to go out. Defau:1. For all but External FIFO, this uses DATACTRL TXTRIG,which defaults to not-full. If DMA is enabled for TX, it will also be signaled to provide more.

fields.name: DACHG
fields.desc: The Slv Dynamic Address has been assigned, reassigned, or reset(lost) and is now in that state of being valid or none. Actual DA can be seen in the DYNADDR register. Note that this will also be used when MAP Auto feature is configured. This will be changing one or more MAP items. See DYNADDR and/or MAPCTRLn. DYNAADDR for the main DA(0) will indicate if last change was due to Auto MAP.

fields.name: CCC
fields.desc: A common -command-code(CCC), not handled by block, has been received. This acts differently between: *Broadcasted ones, which will then also correspond with RXPEND and the 1st byte will be the CCC(command) . *Direct ones, which may never be directed to this device.  If it is, then the TXSEND or RXPEND will be triggered with this end the RXPEND will contain the command.

fields.name: ERRWARN
fields.desc: NA

fields.name: HDRMATCH
fields.desc: NA

fields.name: SLV_EVENT
fields.desc: If set to non-0, will request an event. Once requested, STATUS.EVENT and EVDET will show the status as it progresses. Once completed, the field will automatically return to 0. Once non-0, only 0 can be written(to cancel) until done. 0: Normal mode. If set to 0 after was a non-0 value, will cancel if not already in flight. 1: start an IBI. This will try to push through an IBI on the bus. If data associate with the IBI, it will be drawn from the IBIDATA field. Note that if Time control is enabled, this will include anytime control related bytes  further, the IBIDATA byte will have bit7 set to 1.

fields.name: EXTDATA
fields.desc: reserved

fields.name: MAPIDX
fields.desc: Index of Dynamic Address that IBI is for. This is 0 for the main or base Dynamic Address, or can be any valid index.

fields.name: IBIDATA
fields.desc: Data byte to go with an IBI, if enabled for it. If enabled (was in BCR), then it is required.

fields.name: PENDINT
fields.desc: Should be set to the pending interrupt that GETSTATUS CCC will return. This should be maintained by the application if used and configured, as the Master will read this. If not configured, the GETSTATUS field will return 1 if an IBI is pending, and 0 otherwise.

fields.name: TRANS_START
fields.desc:
Configures to start sending the data in txfifo for slave. 
0: No effect

1: Start

fields.name: TX_LSB_FIRST
fields.desc:
Configures to control the sending order for data needing to be sent. 
1: send data from the least significant bit,

0: send data from the most significant bit.

fields.name: RX_LSB_FIRST
fields.desc:
Configures to control the storage order for received data.
1: receive data from the least significant bit

0: receive data from the most significant bit.

fields.name: CLK_EN
fields.desc:
Configures whether to gate clock signal for registers.

0: Force clock on for registers 

1: Support clock only when registers are read or written to by software.

fields.name: ARBITRATION_EN
fields.desc:
Configures to enable I2C bus arbitration detection.
0: No effect

1: Enable

fields.name: FSM_RST
fields.desc:
Configures to reset the SCL_FSM.
0: No effect

1: Reset

fields.name: CONF_UPGATE
fields.desc:
Configures this bit for synchronization
0: No effect

1: Synchronize

fields.name: RESP_REC
fields.desc:
Represents the received ACK value in master mode or slave mode.
0: ACK,

1: NACK.

fields.name: ARB_LOST
fields.desc:
Represents whether the I2C controller loses control of SCL line.
0: No arbitration lost

1: Arbitration lost

fields.name: BUS_BUSY
fields.desc:
Represents the I2C bus state.
1: The I2C bus is busy transferring data, 

0: The I2C bus is in idle state.

fields.name: RXFIFO_CNT
fields.desc: Represents the number of data bytes to be sent.

fields.name: TXFIFO_CNT
fields.desc: Represents the number of data bytes received in RAM.

fields.name: SCL_MAIN_STATE_LAST
fields.desc:
Represents the states of the I2C module state machine. 
0: Idle,

1: Address shift,

2: ACK address,

3: Rx data,

4: Tx data,

5: Send ACK,

6: Wait ACK

fields.name: SCL_STATE_LAST
fields.desc:
Represents the states of the state machine used to produce SCL.
0: Idle,

1: Start,

2: Negative edge,

3: Low,

4: Positive edge,

5: High,

6: Stop

Configures command 0. It consists of three parts: 
op_code is the command,
0: RSTART, 
1: WRITE,
2: READ,
3: STOP,
4: END.

Byte_num represents the number of bytes that need to be sent or received.
ack_check_en, ack_exp and ack are used to control the ACK bit. See I2C cmd structure for more information.

fields.desc: Set this bit to clear the i2s_rx_fifomem_udf_int interrupt

fields.name: LP_VAD_DONE_INT_CLR
fields.desc: Set this bit to clear the vad_done_int interrupt

fields.name: LP_VAD_RESET_DONE_INT_CLR
fields.desc: Set this bit to clear the vad_reset_done_int interrupt

fields.name: RX_MEM_THRESHOLD_INT_CLR
fields.desc: Set this bit to clear the rx_mem_threshold_int interrupt

fields.name: RX_RESET
fields.desc: Set this bit to reset receiver

fields.name: RX_FIFO_RESET
fields.desc: Set this bit to reset Rx AFIFO

fields.name: RX_START
fields.desc: Set this bit to start receiving data

fields.name: RX_SLAVE_MOD
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable slave receiver mode

fields.name: RX_FIFOMEM_RESET
fields.desc: Set this bit to reset Rx Syncfifomem

fields.name: RX_MONO
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable receiver  in mono mode

fields.name: RX_BIG_ENDIAN
fields.desc: I2S Rx byte endian, 1: low addr value to high addr. 0: low addr with low addr value.

fields.name: RX_UPDATE
fields.desc: Set 1 to update I2S RX registers from APB clock domain to I2S RX clock domain. This bit will be cleared by hardware after update register done.

fields.name: RX_MONO_FST_VLD
fields.desc: 1: The first channel data value is valid in I2S RX mono mode.   0: The second channel data value is valid in I2S RX mono mode.

fields.name: RX_PCM_CONF
fields.desc: I2S RX compress/decompress configuration bit. & 0 (atol): A-Law decompress, 1 (ltoa) : A-Law compress, 2 (utol) : u-Law decompress, 3 (ltou) : u-Law compress. &

fields.name: RX_PCM_BYPASS
fields.desc: Set this bit to bypass Compress/Decompress module for received data.

fields.name: RX_STOP_MODE
fields.desc: 0  : I2S Rx only stop when reg_rx_start is cleared.   1: Stop when reg_rx_start is 0 or in_suc_eof is 1.   2:  Stop I2S RX when reg_rx_start is 0 or RX FIFO is full.

fields.name: RX_LEFT_ALIGN
fields.desc: 1: I2S RX left alignment mode. 0: I2S RX right alignment mode.

fields.name: RX_24_FILL_EN
fields.desc: 1: store 24 channel bits to 32 bits. 0:store 24 channel bits to 24 bits.

fields.name: RX_WS_IDLE_POL
fields.desc: 0: WS should be 0 when receiving left channel data, and WS is 1in right channel.  1: WS should be 1 when receiving left channel data, and WS is 0in right channel.

fields.name: RX_BIT_ORDER
fields.desc: I2S Rx bit endian. 1:small endian, the LSB is received first. 0:big endian, the MSB is received first.

fields.name: RX_TDM_EN
fields.desc: 1: Enable I2S TDM Rx mode . 0: Disable.

fields.name: RX_PDM_EN
fields.desc: 1: Enable I2S PDM Rx mode . 0: Disable.

fields.name: RX_TDM_WS_WIDTH
fields.desc: The width of rx_ws_out in TDM mode is (I2S_RX_TDM_WS_WIDTH[6:0] +1) * T_bck

fields.name: RX_BCK_DIV_NUM
fields.desc: Bit clock configuration bits in receiver mode.

fields.name: RX_BITS_MOD
fields.desc: Set the bits to configure the valid data bit length of I2S receiver channel. 7: all the valid channel data is in 8-bit-mode. 15: all the valid channel data is in 16-bit-mode. 23: all the valid channel data is in 24-bit-mode. 31:all the valid channel data is in 32-bit-mode.

fields.name: RX_HALF_SAMPLE_BITS
fields.desc: I2S Rx half sample bits -1.

fields.name: RX_TDM_CHAN_BITS
fields.desc: The Rx bit number for each channel minus 1in TDM mode.

fields.name: RX_MSB_SHIFT
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable receiver in Phillips standard mode

1343377488.name: RX_TDM_CTRL
1343377488.desc: I2S TX TDM mode control register

fields.name: RX_TDM_PDM_CHAN0_EN
fields.desc: 1: Enable the valid data input of I2S RX TDM or PDM channel 0. 0:  Disable, just input 0 in this channel.

fields.name: RX_TDM_PDM_CHAN1_EN
fields.desc: 1: Enable the valid data input of I2S RX TDM or PDM channel 1. 0:  Disable, just input 0 in this channel.

fields.name: RX_TDM_TOT_CHAN_NUM
fields.desc: The total channel number of I2S TX TDM mode.

fields.name: RX_SD_IN_DM
fields.desc: The delay mode of I2S Rx SD input signal. 0: bypass. 1: delay by pos edge.  2: delay by neg edge. 3: not used.

fields.name: RX_WS_OUT_DM
fields.desc: The delay mode of I2S Rx WS output signal. 0: bypass. 1: delay by pos edge.  2: delay by neg edge. 3: not used.

fields.name: RX_BCK_OUT_DM
fields.desc: The delay mode of I2S Rx BCK output signal. 0: bypass. 1: delay by pos edge.  2: delay by neg edge. 3: not used.

fields.name: RX_WS_IN_DM
fields.desc: The delay mode of I2S Rx WS input signal. 0: bypass. 1: delay by pos edge.  2: delay by neg edge. 3: not used.

fields.name: RX_BCK_IN_DM
fields.desc: The delay mode of I2S Rx BCK input signal. 0: bypass. 1: delay by pos edge.  2: delay by neg edge. 3: not used.

fields.name: LC_FIFO_TIMEOUT
fields.desc: the i2s_tx_hung_int interrupt or the i2s_rx_hung_int interrupt will be triggered when fifo hung counter is equal to this value

fields.name: LC_FIFO_TIMEOUT_SHIFT
fields.desc: The bits are used to scale tick counter threshold. The tick counter is reset when counter value >= 88000/2^i2s_lc_fifo_timeout_shift

fields.name: LC_FIFO_TIMEOUT_ENA
fields.desc: The enable bit for FIFO timeout

1343377508.name: RXEOF_NUM
1343377508.desc: I2S RX data number control register.

fields.name: RX_EOF_NUM
fields.desc: The receive data bit length is (I2S_RX_BITS_MOD[4:0] + 1) * (REG_RX_EOF_NUM[11:0] + 1) . It will trigger in_suc_eof interrupt in the configured DMA RX channel.

fields.name: SINGLE_DATA
fields.desc: The configured constant channel data to be sent out.

fields.name: RX_PDM2PCM_EN
fields.desc: 1: Enable PDM2PCM RX mode. 0: DIsable.

fields.name: RX_PDM_SINC_DSR_16_EN
fields.desc: Configure the down sampling rate of PDM RX filter group1 module. 1: The  down sampling rate is 128. 0: down sampling rate is 64.

fields.name: RX_PDM2PCM_AMPLIFY_NUM
fields.desc: Configure PDM RX amplify number.

fields.name: RX_PDM_HP_BYPASS
fields.desc: I2S PDM RX bypass hp filter or not.

fields.name: RX_IIR_HP_MULT12_5
fields.desc: The fourth parameter of PDM RX IIR_HP filter stage 2 is (504 + LP_I2S_RX_IIR_HP_MULT12_5[2:0])

fields.name: RX_IIR_HP_MULT12_0
fields.desc: The fourth parameter of PDM RX IIR_HP filter stage 1 is (504 + LP_I2S_RX_IIR_HP_MULT12_0[2:0])

fields.name: RXFIFO_RD_BYTE
fields.desc: UART 0 accesses FIFO via this register.

fields.name: RXFIFO_FULL_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver receives more data than what rxfifo_full_thrhd specifies.

fields.name: TXFIFO_EMPTY_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when the amount of data in Tx-FIFO is less than what txfifo_empty_thrhd specifies .

fields.name: PARITY_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects a parity error in the data.

fields.name: FRM_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects a data frame error .

fields.name: RXFIFO_OVF_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver receives more data than the FIFO can store.

fields.name: DSR_CHG_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects the edge change of DSRn signal.

fields.name: CTS_CHG_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects the edge change of CTSn signal.

fields.name: BRK_DET_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects a 0 after the stop bit.

fields.name: RXFIFO_TOUT_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver takes more time than rx_tout_thrhd to receive a byte.

fields.name: SW_XON_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver recevies Xon char when uart_sw_flow_con_en is set to 1.

fields.name: SW_XOFF_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver receives Xoff char when uart_sw_flow_con_en is set to 1.

fields.name: GLITCH_DET_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when receiver detects a glitch in the middle of a start bit.

fields.name: TX_BRK_DONE_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when transmitter completes  sending  NULL characters after all data in Tx-FIFO are sent.

fields.name: TX_BRK_IDLE_DONE_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when transmitter has kept the shortest duration after sending the  last data.

fields.name: TX_DONE_INT_RAW
fields.desc: This interrupt raw bit turns to high level when transmitter has send out all data in FIFO.

fields.name: AT_CMD_CHAR_DET_INT_RAW
