fields.name: CLKDIV
fields.desc: The integral part of the frequency divider factor.

fields.name: CLKDIV_FRAG
fields.desc: The decimal part of the frequency divider factor.

fields.name: GLITCH_FILT
fields.desc: when input pulse width is lower than this value the pulse is ignored.

fields.name: GLITCH_FILT_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable Rx signal filter.

fields.name: RXFIFO_CNT
fields.desc: Stores the byte number of valid data in Rx-FIFO.

fields.name: DSRN
fields.desc: The register represent the level value of the internal uart dsr signal.

fields.name: CTSN
fields.desc: This register represent the level value of the internal uart cts signal.

fields.name: RXD
fields.desc: This register represent the  level value of the internal uart rxd signal.

fields.name: TXFIFO_CNT
fields.desc: Stores the byte number of data in Tx-FIFO.

fields.name: DTRN
fields.desc: This bit represents the level of the internal uart dtr signal.

fields.name: RTSN
fields.desc: This bit represents the level of the internal uart rts signal.

fields.name: TXD
fields.desc: This bit represents the  level of the internal uart txd signal.

fields.name: PARITY
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the parity check mode.

fields.name: PARITY_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable uart parity check.

fields.name: BIT_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to set the length of data.

fields.name: STOP_BIT_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to set the length of  stop bit.

fields.name: TXD_BRK
fields.desc: Set this bit to enbale transmitter to  send NULL when the process of sending data is done.

fields.name: LOOPBACK
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable uart loopback test mode.

fields.name: TX_FLOW_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable flow control function for transmitter.

fields.name: RXD_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart rxd signal.

fields.name: TXD_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart txd signal.

fields.name: DIS_RX_DAT_OVF
fields.desc: Disable UART Rx data overflow detect.

fields.name: ERR_WR_MASK
fields.desc: 1'h1: Receiver stops storing data into FIFO when data is wrong. 1'h0: Receiver stores the data even if the  received data is wrong.

fields.name: MEM_CLK_EN
fields.desc: UART memory clock gate enable signal.

fields.name: SW_RTS
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the software rts signal which is used in software flow control.

fields.name: RXFIFO_RST
fields.desc: Set this bit to reset the uart receive-FIFO.

fields.name: TXFIFO_RST
fields.desc: Set this bit to reset the uart transmit-FIFO.

fields.name: RXFIFO_FULL_THRHD
fields.desc: It will produce rxfifo_full_int interrupt when receiver receives more data than this register value.

fields.name: TXFIFO_EMPTY_THRHD
fields.desc: It will produce txfifo_empty_int interrupt when the data amount in Tx-FIFO is less than this register value.

fields.name: CTS_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart cts signal.

fields.name: DSR_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart dsr signal.

fields.name: RTS_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart rts signal.

fields.name: DTR_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to inverse the level value of uart dtr signal.

fields.name: SW_DTR
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the software dtr signal which is used in software flow control.

fields.name: CLK_EN
fields.desc: 1'h1: Force clock on for register. 1'h0: Support clock only when application writes registers.

fields.name: RX_FLOW_THRHD
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the maximum amount of data that can be received  when hardware flow control works.

fields.name: RX_FLOW_EN
fields.desc: This is the flow enable bit for UART receiver.

fields.name: WK_CHAR1
fields.desc: This register restores the specified wake up char1 to wake up

fields.name: WK_CHAR2
fields.desc: This register restores the specified wake up char2 to wake up

fields.name: WK_CHAR3
fields.desc: This register restores the specified wake up char3 to wake up

fields.name: WK_CHAR4
fields.desc: This register restores the specified wake up char4 to wake up

fields.name: WK_CHAR0
fields.desc: This register restores the specified char0 to wake up

fields.name: ACTIVE_THRESHOLD
fields.desc: The uart is activated from light sleeping mode when the input rxd edge changes more times than this register value.

fields.name: RX_WAKE_UP_THRHD
fields.desc: In wake up mode 1 this field is used to set the received data number threshold to wake up chip.

fields.name: WK_CHAR_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to select number of wake up char.

fields.name: WK_CHAR_MASK
fields.desc: This register is used to mask  wake up char.

fields.name: WK_MODE_SEL
fields.desc: This register is used to select wake up mode. 0: RXD toggling to wake up. 1: received data number larger than

fields.name: XON_CHAR
fields.desc: This register stores the Xon flow control char.

fields.name: XOFF_CHAR
fields.desc: This register stores the Xoff flow control char.

fields.name: XON_XOFF_STILL_SEND
fields.desc: In software flow control mode, UART Tx is disabled once UART Rx receives XOFF. In this status, UART Tx can not transmit XOFF even the received data number is larger than UART_XOFF_THRESHOLD. Set this bit to enable UART Tx can transmit XON/XOFF when UART Tx is disabled.

fields.name: SW_FLOW_CON_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable software flow control. It is used with register sw_xon or sw_xoff.

fields.name: XONOFF_DEL
fields.desc: Set this bit to remove flow control char from the received data.

fields.name: FORCE_XON
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable the transmitter to go on sending data.

fields.name: FORCE_XOFF
fields.desc: Set this bit to stop the  transmitter from sending data.

fields.name: SEND_XON
fields.desc: Set this bit to send Xon char. It is cleared by hardware automatically.

fields.name: SEND_XOFF
fields.desc: Set this bit to send Xoff char. It is cleared by hardware automatically.

fields.name: XON_THRESHOLD
fields.desc: When the data amount in Rx-FIFO is less than this register value with uart_sw_flow_con_en set to 1  it will send a Xon char.

fields.name: XOFF_THRESHOLD
fields.desc: When the data amount in Rx-FIFO is more than this register value with uart_sw_flow_con_en set to 1  it will send a Xoff char.

fields.name: TX_BRK_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the number of 0 to be sent after the process of sending data is done. It is active when txd_brk is set to 1.

fields.name: RX_IDLE_THRHD
fields.desc: It will produce frame end signal when receiver takes more time to receive one byte data than this register value.

fields.name: TX_IDLE_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the duration time between transfers.

fields.name: DL0_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to delay the stop bit by 1 bit.

fields.name: DL1_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to delay the stop bit by 1 bit.

fields.name: PRE_IDLE_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the idle duration time before the first at_cmd is received by receiver.

fields.name: POST_IDLE_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the duration time between the last at_cmd and the next data.

fields.name: RX_GAP_TOUT
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the duration time between the at_cmd chars.

fields.name: AT_CMD_CHAR
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the content of at_cmd char.

fields.name: CHAR_NUM
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the num of continuous at_cmd chars received by receiver.

fields.name: MEM_FORCE_PD
fields.desc: Set this bit to force power down UART memory.

fields.name: MEM_FORCE_PU
fields.desc: Set this bit to force power up UART memory.

fields.name: RX_TOUT_EN
fields.desc: This is the enble bit for uart receiver's timeout function.

fields.name: RX_TOUT_FLOW_DIS
fields.desc: Set this bit to stop accumulating idle_cnt when hardware flow control works.

fields.name: RX_TOUT_THRHD
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the threshold time that receiver takes to receive one byte. The rxfifo_tout_int interrupt will be trigger when the receiver takes more time to receive one byte with rx_tout_en set to 1.

1343361128.name: MEM_TX_STATUS
1343361128.desc: Tx-SRAM write and read offset address.

fields.name: TX_SRAM_WADDR
fields.desc: This register stores the offset write address in Tx-SRAM.

fields.name: TX_SRAM_RADDR
fields.desc: This register stores the offset read address in Tx-SRAM.

1343361132.name: MEM_RX_STATUS
1343361132.desc: Rx-SRAM write and read offset address.

fields.name: RX_SRAM_RADDR
fields.desc: This register stores the offset read address in RX-SRAM.

fields.name: RX_SRAM_WADDR
fields.desc: This register stores the offset write address in Rx-SRAM.

fields.name: ST_URX_OUT
fields.desc: This is the status register of receiver.

fields.name: ST_UTX_OUT
fields.desc: This is the status register of transmitter.

fields.name: TX_SCLK_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable UART Tx clock.

fields.name: RX_SCLK_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable UART Rx clock.

fields.name: TX_RST_CORE
fields.desc: Write 1 then write 0 to this bit to reset UART Tx.

fields.name: RX_RST_CORE
fields.desc: Write 1 then write 0 to this bit to reset UART Rx.

fields.name: DATE
fields.desc: This is the version register.

fields.name: TX_AFIFO_FULL
fields.desc: Full signal of APB TX AFIFO.

fields.name: TX_AFIFO_EMPTY
fields.desc: Empty signal of APB TX AFIFO.

fields.name: RX_AFIFO_FULL
fields.desc: Full signal of APB RX AFIFO.

fields.name: RX_AFIFO_EMPTY
fields.desc: Empty signal of APB RX AFIFO.

fields.name: REG_UPDATE
fields.desc: Software write 1 would synchronize registers into UART Core clock domain and would be cleared by hardware after synchronization is done.

fields.name: ID
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the uart_id.

fields.name: CLK_PRESCALE
fields.desc: Configures the prescaler value of clock, so that the period of PWM_clk = 6.25ns * (PWM_CLK_PRESCALE + 1).

1342963716.name: TIMER%s_CFG0
1342963716.desc: PWM timer%s period and update method configuration register.

fields.name: TIMER_PRESCALE
fields.desc: Configures the prescaler value of timer%s, so that the period of PT0_clk = Period of PWM_clk * (PWM_TIMER%s_PRESCALE + 1)

fields.name: TIMER_PERIOD
fields.desc: Configures the period shadow of PWM timer%s

fields.name: TIMER_PERIOD_UPMETHOD
fields.desc: Configures the update method for active register of PWM timer%s period.\\0: Immediate\\1: TEZ\\2: Sync\\3: TEZ or sync\\TEZ here and below means timer equal zero event

1342963720.name: TIMER%s_CFG1
1342963720.desc: PWM timer%s working mode and start/stop control register.

fields.name: TIMER_START
fields.desc: Configures whether or not to start/stop PWM timer%s.\\0: If PWM timer%s starts, then stops at TEZ\\1: If timer%s starts, then stops at TEP\\2: PWM timer%s starts and runs on\\3: Timer%s starts and stops at the next TEZ\\4: Timer0 starts and stops at the next TEP.\\TEP here and below means the event that happens when the timer equals to period

fields.name: TIMER_MOD
fields.desc: Configures the working mode of PWM timer%s.\\0: Freeze\\1: Increase mode\\2: Decrease mode\\3: Up-down mode

1342963724.name: TIMER%s_SYNC
1342963724.desc: PWM timer%s sync function configuration register.

fields.name: TIMER_SYNCI_EN
fields.desc: Configures whether or not to enable timer%s reloading with phase on sync input event is enabled.\\0: Disable\\1: Enable

fields.name: SW
fields.desc: Configures the generation of software sync. Toggling this bit will trigger a software sync.

fields.name: TIMER_SYNCO_SEL
fields.desc: Configures the selection of PWM timer%s sync_out.\\0: Sync_in\\1: TEZ\\2: TEP\\3: Invalid, sync_out selects noting

fields.name: TIMER_PHASE
fields.desc: Configures the phase for timer%s reload on sync event.

fields.name: TIMER_PHASE_DIRECTION
fields.desc: Configures the PWM timer%s's direction when timer%s mode is up-down mode.\\0: Increase\\1: Decrease

fields.name: TIMER_VALUE
fields.desc: Represents current PWM timer%s counter value.

fields.name: TIMER_DIRECTION
fields.desc: Represents current PWM timer%s counter direction.\\0: Increment\\1: Decrement

1342963764.name: TIMER_SYNCI_CFG
1342963764.desc: Synchronization input selection register for PWM timers.

fields.name: TIMER0_SYNCISEL
fields.desc: Configures the selection of sync input for PWM timer0.\\1: PWM timer0 sync_out\\2: PWM timer1 sync_out\\3: PWM timer2 sync_out\\4: SYNC0 from GPIO matrix\\5: SYNC1 from GPIO matrix\\6: SYNC2 from GPIO matrix\\Other values: No sync input selected

fields.name: TIMER1_SYNCISEL
fields.desc: Configures the selection of sync input for PWM timer1.\\1: PWM timer0 sync_out\\2: PWM timer1 sync_out\\3: PWM timer2 sync_out\\4: SYNC0 from GPIO matrix\\5: SYNC1 from GPIO matrix\\6: SYNC2 from GPIO matrix\\Other values: No sync input selected

fields.name: TIMER2_SYNCISEL
fields.desc: Configures the selection of sync input for PWM timer2.\\1: PWM timer0 sync_out\\2: PWM timer1 sync_out\\3: PWM timer2 sync_out\\4: SYNC0 from GPIO matrix\\5: SYNC1 from GPIO matrix\\6: SYNC2 from GPIO matrix\\Other values: No sync input selected

fields.name: EXTERNAL_SYNCI0_INVERT
fields.desc: Configures whether or not to invert SYNC0 from GPIO matrix.\\0: Not invert\\1: Invert

fields.name: EXTERNAL_SYNCI1_INVERT
fields.desc: Configures whether or not to invert SYNC1 from GPIO matrix.\\0: Not invert\\1: Invert

fields.name: EXTERNAL_SYNCI2_INVERT
fields.desc: Configures whether or not to invert SYNC2 from GPIO matrix.\\0: Not invert\\1: Invert

fields.name: OPERATOR0_TIMERSEL
fields.desc: Configures which PWM timer will be the timing reference for PWM operator0.\\0: Timer0\\1: Timer1\\2: Timer2\\3: Invalid, will select timer2

fields.name: OPERATOR1_TIMERSEL
fields.desc: Configures which PWM timer will be the timing reference for PWM operator1.\\0: Timer0\\1: Timer1\\2: Timer2\\3: Invalid, will select timer2

fields.name: OPERATOR2_TIMERSEL
fields.desc: Configures which PWM timer will be the timing reference for PWM operator2.\\0: Timer0\\1: Timer1\\2: Timer2\\3: Invalid, will select timer2

1342963772.name: GEN%s_STMP_CFG
1342963772.desc: Generator%s time stamp registers A and B transfer status and update method register

fields.name: CMPR_A_UPMETHOD
fields.desc: Configures the update method for PWM generator %s time stamp A's active register.\\0: Immediately\\Bit0 is set to 1: TEZ\\Bit1 is set to 1: TEP\\Bit2 is set to 1: Sync\\Bit3 is set to 1: Disable the update

fields.name: CMPR_B_UPMETHOD
fields.desc: Configures the update method for PWM generator %s time stamp B's active register.\\0: Immediately\\Bit0 is set to 1: TEZ\\Bit1 is set to 1: TEP\\Bit2 is set to 1: Sync\\Bit3 is set to 1: Disable the update

fields.name: CMPR_A_SHDW_FULL
fields.desc: Represents whether or not generator%s time stamp A's shadow reg is transferred.\\0: A's active reg has been updated with shadow register latest value.\\1: A's shadow reg is filled and waiting to be transferred to A's active reg

fields.name: CMPR_B_SHDW_FULL
fields.desc: Represents whether or not generator%s time stamp B's shadow reg is transferred.\\0: B's active reg has been updated with shadow register latest value.\\1: B's shadow reg is filled and waiting to be transferred to B's active reg

1342963776.name: GEN%s_TSTMP_A
1342963776.desc: Generator%s time stamp A's shadow register

fields.name: CMPR_A
fields.desc: Configures the value of PWM generator %s time stamp A's shadow register.

1342963780.name: GEN%s_TSTMP_B
1342963780.desc: Generator%s time stamp B's shadow register

fields.name: CMPR_B
fields.desc: Configures the value of PWM generator %s time stamp B's shadow register.

1342963784.name: GEN%s_CFG0
1342963784.desc: Generator%s fault event T0 and T1 configuration register

fields.name: GEN_CFG_UPMETHOD
fields.desc: Configures update method for PWM generator %s's active register.\\0: Immediately\\Bit0 is set to 1: TEZ\\Bit1 is set to 1: TEP\\Bit2 is set to 1: Sync\\Bit3 is set to 1: Disable the update

fields.name: GEN_T0_SEL
fields.desc: Configures source selection for PWM generator %s event_t0, take effect immediately.\\0: fault_event0\\1: fault_event1\\2: fault_event2\\3: sync_taken\\4: Invalid, Select nothing

fields.name: GEN_T1_SEL
fields.desc: Configures source selection for PWM generator %s event_t1, take effect immediately.\\0: fault_event0\\1: fault_event1\\2: fault_event2\\3: sync_taken\\4: Invalid, Select nothing

1342963788.name: GEN%s_FORCE
1342963788.desc: Generator%s output signal force mode register.

fields.name: GEN_CNTUFORCE_UPMETHOD
fields.desc: Configures update method for continuous software force of PWM generator%s.\\0: Immediately\\Bit0 is set to 1: TEZ\\Bit1 is set to 1: TEP\\Bit2 is set to 1: TEA\\Bit3 is set to 1: TEB\\Bit4 is set to 1: Sync\\Bit5 is set to 1: Disable update. TEA/B here and below means an event generated when the timer's value equals to that of register A/B.

fields.name: GEN_A_CNTUFORCE_MODE
fields.desc: Configures continuous software force mode for PWM%s A.\\0: Disabled\\1: Low\\2: High\\3: Disabled

fields.name: GEN_B_CNTUFORCE_MODE
fields.desc: Configures continuous software force mode for PWM%s B.\\0: Disabled\\1: Low\\2: High\\3: Disabled

fields.name: GEN_A_NCIFORCE
fields.desc: Configures the generation of non-continuous immediate software-force event for PWM%s A, a toggle will trigger a force event.

fields.name: GEN_A_NCIFORCE_MODE
fields.desc: Configures non-continuous immediate software force mode for PWM%s A.\\0: Disabled\\1: Low\\2: High\\3: Disabled

fields.name: GEN_B_NCIFORCE
fields.desc: Configures the generation of non-continuous immediate software-force event for PWM%s B, a toggle will trigger a force event.

fields.name: GEN_B_NCIFORCE_MODE
fields.desc: Configures non-continuous immediate software force mode for PWM%s B.\\0: Disabled\\1: Low\\2: High\\3: Disabled

1342963792.name: GEN%s_A
1342963792.desc: PWM%s output signal A actions configuration register

fields.name: RX_PULSE_SUBMODE_SEL
fields.desc:
Configures the rxd pulse sampling submode. 
4'd0: positive pulse start(data bit included) &&  positive pulse end(data bit included)
4'd1: positive pulse start(data bit included) && positive pulse end (data bit excluded)
4'd2: positive pulse start(data bit excluded) && positive pulse end (data bit included)
4'd3: positive pulse start(data bit excluded) && positive pulse end (data bit excluded)
4'd4: positive pulse start(data bit included) && length end
4'd5: positive pulse start(data bit excluded) && length end

2'b00: external level enable mode
2'b01: external pulse enable mode  
2'b10: internal software enable mode

1: Increase the counter.2: Decrease the counter.0, 3: No effect on counter

0: No modification.1: Invert behavior (increase -> decrease, decrease -> increase).2, 3: Inhibit counter modification

0: No modification.1: Invert behavior (increase -> decrease, decrease -> increase).2, 3: Inhibit counter modification

fields.name: CH1_NEG_MODE_U
fields.desc:
This register sets the behavior when the signal input of channel 1 detects a negative edge.

1: Increment the counter.2: Decrement the counter.0, 3: No effect on counter

fields.name: CH1_POS_MODE_U
fields.desc:
This register sets the behavior when the signal input of channel 1 detects a positive edge.

1: Increment the counter.2: Decrement the counter.0, 3: No effect on counter

fields.name: CH1_HCTRL_MODE_U
fields.desc:
This register configures how the CH%s_POS_MODE/CH%s_NEG_MODE settings will be modified when the control signal is high.

0: No modification.1: Invert behavior (increase -> decrease, decrease -> increase).2, 3: Inhibit counter modification

fields.name: CH1_LCTRL_MODE_U
fields.desc:
This register configures how the CH%s_POS_MODE/CH%s_NEG_MODE settings will be modified when the control signal is low.

0: No modification.1: Invert behavior (increase -> decrease, decrease -> increase).2, 3: Inhibit counter modification

fields.name: CNT_THRES0_U
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the thres0 value for unit %s.

fields.name: CNT_THRES1_U
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the thres1 value for unit %s.

fields.name: CNT_H_LIM_U
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the thr_h_lim value for unit %s. When pcnt reaches this value, the counter will be cleared to 0.

fields.name: CNT_L_LIM_U
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the thr_l_lim value for unit %s. When pcnt reaches this value, the counter will be cleared to 0.

fields.name: PULSE_CNT_U
fields.desc: This register stores the current pulse count value for unit %s.

fields.name: CNT_THR_ZERO_MODE_U
fields.desc: The pulse counter status of PCNT_U%s corresponding to 0. 0: pulse counter decreases from positive to 0. 1: pulse counter increases from negative to 0. 2: pulse counter is negative. 3: pulse counter is positive.

fields.name: CNT_THR_THRES1_LAT_U
fields.desc: The latched value of thres1 event of PCNT_U%s when threshold event interrupt is valid. 1: the current pulse counter equals to thres1 and thres1 event is valid. 0: others

fields.name: CNT_THR_THRES0_LAT_U
fields.desc: The latched value of thres0 event of PCNT_U%s when threshold event interrupt is valid. 1: the current pulse counter equals to thres0 and thres0 event is valid. 0: others

fields.name: CNT_THR_L_LIM_LAT_U
fields.desc: The latched value of low limit event of PCNT_U%s when threshold event interrupt is valid. 1: the current pulse counter equals to thr_l_lim and low limit event is valid. 0: others

fields.name: CNT_THR_H_LIM_LAT_U
fields.desc: The latched value of high limit event of PCNT_U%s when threshold event interrupt is valid. 1: the current pulse counter equals to thr_h_lim and high limit event is valid. 0: others

fields.name: CNT_THR_ZERO_LAT_U
fields.desc: The latched value of zero threshold event of PCNT_U%s when threshold event interrupt is valid. 1: the current pulse counter equals to 0 and zero threshold event is valid. 0: others

1342730240.name: BLEND0_CLUT_DATA
1342730240.desc: CLUT sram data read/write register in background plane of blender

fields.name: RDWR_WORD_BLEND0_CLUT
fields.desc: Write and read data to/from CLUT RAM in background plane of blender engine through this field in fifo mode.

1342730244.name: BLEND1_CLUT_DATA
1342730244.desc: CLUT sram data read/write register in foreground plane of blender

fields.name: RDWR_WORD_BLEND1_CLUT
fields.desc: Write and read data to/from CLUT RAM in foreground plane of blender engine through this field in fifo mode.

fields.name: APB_FIFO_MASK
fields.desc: 1'b0: fifo mode to wr/rd clut0/clut1 RAM through register PPA_SR_CLUT_DATA_REG/PPA_BLEND0_CLUT_DATA_REG/PPA_BLEND1_CLUT_DATA_REG. 1'b1: memory mode to wr/rd sr/blend0/blend1 clut RAM. The bit 11 and 10 of the waddr should be 01 to access sr clut and should be 10 to access blend0 clut and should be 11 to access blend 1 clut in memory mode.

fields.name: BLEND0_CLUT_MEM_RST
fields.desc: Write 1 then write 0 to this bit to reset BLEND0 CLUT.

fields.name: BLEND1_CLUT_MEM_RST
fields.desc: Write 1 then write 0 to this bit to reset BLEND1 CLUT.

fields.name: BLEND0_CLUT_MEM_RDADDR_RST
fields.desc: Write 1 then write 0 to reset the read address of BLEND0 CLUT in fifo mode.

fields.name: BLEND1_CLUT_MEM_RDADDR_RST
fields.desc: Write 1 then write 0 to reset the read address of BLEND1 CLUT in fifo mode.

fields.name: BLEND0_CLUT_MEM_FORCE_PD
fields.desc: 1: force power down BLEND CLUT memory.

fields.name: BLEND0_CLUT_MEM_FORCE_PU
fields.desc: 1: force power up BLEND CLUT memory.

fields.name: BLEND0_CLUT_MEM_CLK_ENA
fields.desc: 1: Force clock on for BLEND CLUT memory.

fields.name: SR_EOF_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when scaling and rotating engine calculate one frame image.

fields.name: BLEND_EOF_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when blending engine calculate one frame image.

fields.name: SR_PARAM_CFG_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw interrupt bit turns to high level when the configured scaling and rotating coefficient is wrong. User can check the reasons through register PPA_SR_PARAM_ERR_ST_REG.

fields.name: SR_EOF_INT_ST
fields.desc: The raw interrupt status bit for the PPA_SR_EOF_INT interrupt.

fields.name: BLEND_EOF_INT_ST
fields.desc: The raw interrupt status bit for the PPA_BLEND_EOF_INT interrupt.

fields.name: SR_PARAM_CFG_ERR_INT_ST
fields.desc: The raw interrupt status bit for the PPA_SR_RX_YSCAL_ERR_INT interrupt.

fields.name: SR_EOF_INT_ENA
fields.desc: The interrupt enable bit for the PPA_SR_EOF_INT interrupt.

fields.name: BLEND_EOF_INT_ENA
fields.desc: The interrupt enable bit for the PPA_BLEND_EOF_INT interrupt.

fields.name: SR_PARAM_CFG_ERR_INT_ENA
fields.desc: The interrupt enable bit for the PPA_SR_RX_YSCAL_ERR_INT interrupt.

fields.name: SR_EOF_INT_CLR
fields.desc: Set this bit to clear the PPA_SR_EOF_INT interrupt.

fields.name: BLEND_EOF_INT_CLR
fields.desc: Set this bit to clear the PPA_BLEND_EOF_INT interrupt.

fields.name: SR_PARAM_CFG_ERR_INT_CLR
fields.desc: Set this bit to clear the PPA_SR_RX_YSCAL_ERR_INT interrupt.

1342730272.name: SR_COLOR_MODE
1342730272.desc: Scaling and rotating engine color mode register

fields.name: SR_RX_CM
fields.desc: The source image color mode for Scaling and Rotating engine Rx. 0: ARGB8888. 1: RGB888. 2: RGB565. 8: YUV420. others: Reserved.

fields.name: SR_TX_CM
fields.desc: The destination image color mode for Scaling and Rotating engine Tx. 0: ARGB8888. 1: RGB888. 2: RGB565. 8: YUV420. others: Reserved.

fields.name: YUV_RX_RANGE
fields.desc: YUV input range when reg_sr_rx_cm is 4'd8. 0: limit range. 1: full range

fields.name: YUV_TX_RANGE
fields.desc: YUV output range when reg_sr_tx_cm is 4'd8. 0: limit range. 1: full range

fields.name: YUV2RGB_PROTOCAL
fields.desc: YUV to RGB protocal when reg_sr_rx_cm is 4'd8. 0: BT601. 1: BT709

fields.name: RGB2YUV_PROTOCAL
fields.desc: RGB to YUV protocal when reg_sr_tx_cm is 4'd8. 0: BT601. 1: BT709

fields.name: BLEND0_RX_CM
fields.desc: The source image color mode for background plane. 0: ARGB8888. 1: RGB888. 2: RGB565. 3: Reserved. 4: L8. 5: L4.

fields.name: BLEND1_RX_CM
fields.desc: The source image color mode for foreground plane. 0: ARGB8888. 1: RGB888. 2: RGB565. 3: Reserved. 4: L8. 5: L4. 6: A8. 7: A4.

fields.name: BLEND_TX_CM
fields.desc: The destination image color mode for output of blender. 0: ARGB8888. 1: RGB888. 2: RGB565. 3: Reserved..

1342730280.name: SR_BYTE_ORDER
1342730280.desc: Scaling and rotating engine byte order register

fields.name: SR_RX_BYTE_SWAP_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to 1  the data into Rx channel 0 would be swapped in byte. The Byte0 and Byte1 would be swapped while byte 2 and byte 3 would be swappped.

fields.name: SR_RX_RGB_SWAP_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to 1  the data into Rx channel 0 would be swapped in rgb. It means rgb would be swap to bgr.

fields.name: SR_MACRO_BK_RO_BYPASS
fields.desc: Set this bit to 1 to bypass the macro block order function. This function is used to improve efficient accessing external memory.

fields.name: BLEND0_RX_BYTE_SWAP_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to 1  the data into Rx channel 0 would be swapped in byte. The Byte0 and Byte1 would be swapped while byte 2 and byte 3 would be swappped.

fields.name: BLEND1_RX_BYTE_SWAP_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to 1  the data into Rx channel 0 would be swapped in byte. The Byte0 and Byte1 would be swapped while byte 2 and byte 3 would be swappped.

fields.name: BLEND0_RX_RGB_SWAP_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to 1  the data into Rx channel 0 would be swapped in rgb. It means rgb would be swap to bgr.

fields.name: BLEND1_RX_RGB_SWAP_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to 1  the data into Rx channel 0 would be swapped in rgb. It means rgb would be swap to bgr.

fields.name: BLEND_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable alpha blending.

fields.name: BLEND_BYPASS
fields.desc: Set this bit to bypass blender. Then background date would be output.

fields.name: BLEND_FIX_PIXEL_FILL_EN
fields.desc: This bit is used to enable fix pixel filling. When this mode is enable  only Tx channel is work and the output pixel is configured by PPA_OUT_FIX_PIXEL.

fields.name: UPDATE
fields.desc: Set this bit to update the transfer mode. Only the bit is set  the transfer mode is valid.

fields.name: BLEND_RST
fields.desc: write 1 then write 0 to reset blending engine.

1342730296.name: SR_FIX_ALPHA
1342730296.desc: Scaling and rotating engine alpha override register

fields.name: SR_RX_FIX_ALPHA
fields.desc: The value would replace the alpha value in received pixel for Scaling and Rotating engine when PPA_SR_RX_ALPHA_CONF_EN is enabled.

fields.name: SR_RX_ALPHA_MOD
fields.desc: Alpha mode. 0/3: not replace alpha. 1: replace alpha with PPA_SR_FIX_ALPHA. 2: Original alpha multiply with PPA_SR_FIX_ALPHA/256.

fields.name: SR_RX_ALPHA_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to invert the original alpha value. When RX color mode is RGB565/RGB88. The original alpha value is 255.

1342730300.name: BLEND_TX_SIZE
1342730300.desc: Fix pixel filling mode image size register

fields.name: BLEND_HB
fields.desc: The horizontal width of image block that would be filled in fix pixel filling mode. The unit is pixel

fields.name: BLEND_VB
fields.desc: The vertical width of image block that would be filled in fix pixel filling mode. The unit is pixel

fields.name: BLEND0_RX_FIX_ALPHA
fields.desc: The value would replace the alpha value in received pixel for background plane of blender when PPA_BLEND0_RX_ALPHA_CONF_EN is enabled.

fields.name: BLEND1_RX_FIX_ALPHA
fields.desc: The value would replace the alpha value in received pixel for foreground plane of blender when PPA_BLEND1_RX_ALPHA_CONF_EN is enabled.

fields.name: BLEND0_RX_ALPHA_MOD
fields.desc: Alpha mode. 0/3: not replace alpha. 1: replace alpha with PPA_SR_FIX_ALPHA. 2: Original alpha multiply with PPA_SR_FIX_ALPHA/256.

fields.name: BLEND1_RX_ALPHA_MOD
fields.desc: Alpha mode. 0/3: not replace alpha. 1: replace alpha with PPA_SR_FIX_ALPHA. 2: Original alpha multiply with PPA_SR_FIX_ALPHA/256.

fields.name: BLEND0_RX_ALPHA_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to invert the original alpha value. When RX color mode is RGB565/RGB88. The original alpha value is 255.

fields.name: BLEND1_RX_ALPHA_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to invert the original alpha value. When RX color mode is RGB565/RGB88. The original alpha value is 255.

fields.name: BLEND1_RX_B
fields.desc: blue color for A4/A8 mode.

fields.name: BLEND1_RX_G
fields.desc: green color for A4/A8 mode.

fields.name: BLEND1_RX_R
fields.desc: red color for A4/A8 mode.

fields.name: BLEND_TX_FIX_PIXEL
fields.desc: The configure fix pixel in fix pixel filling mode for blender engine.

fields.name: SR_SCAL_X_INT

fields.name: SR_SCAL_Y_FRAG

fields.name: SR_ROTATE_ANGLE
fields.desc: The rotate angle. 0: 0 degree. 1: 90 degree. 2: 180 degree. 3: 270 degree.

fields.name: SCAL_ROTATE_RST
fields.desc: Write 1 then write 0 to this bit to reset scaling and rotating engine.

fields.name: SCAL_ROTATE_START
fields.desc: Write 1 to enable scaling and rotating engine after parameter is configured.

fields.name: SR_MIRROR_X

fields.name: SR_MIRROR_Y

fields.name: SR_MEM_CLK_ENA

fields.desc: Set this bit to force power up scaling and rotating engine's data memory.

1342730360.name: SR_PARAM_ERR_ST
1342730360.desc: Scaling and rotating coefficient error register

fields.name: TX_DSCR_VB_ERR_ST
fields.desc: The error is that the scaled VB plus the offset of Y coordinate in 2DDMA receive descriptor is larger than VA in 2DDMA receive descriptor.

fields.name: TX_DSCR_HB_ERR_ST
fields.desc: The error is that the scaled HB plus the offset of X coordinate in 2DDMA receive descriptor is larger than HA in 2DDMA receive descriptor.

fields.name: Y_RX_SCAL_EQUAL_0_ERR_ST
fields.desc: The error is that the PPA_SR_SCAL_Y_INT and PPA_SR_CAL_Y_FRAG both are 0.

fields.name: RX_DSCR_VB_ERR_ST
fields.desc: The error is that VB in 2DDMA receive descriptor plus the offset of Y coordinate in 2DDMA transmit descriptor is larger than VA in 2DDMA transmit descriptor

fields.name: YDST_LEN_TOO_SAMLL_ERR_ST
fields.desc: The error is that the scaled image width is 0. For example.  when source width is 14. scaled value is 1/16. and no rotate operation. then scaled width would be 0 as the result would be floored.

fields.name: YDST_LEN_TOO_LARGE_ERR_ST
fields.desc: The error is that the scaled width is larger than (2^13 - 1).

fields.name: X_RX_SCAL_EQUAL_0_ERR_ST
fields.desc: The error is that the scaled image height is 0.

fields.name: RX_DSCR_HB_ERR_ST
fields.desc: The error is that the HB in 2DDMA transmit descriptor plus the offset of X coordinate in 2DDMA transmit descriptor is larger than HA in 2DDMA transmit descriptor.

fields.name: XDST_LEN_TOO_SAMLL_ERR_ST
fields.desc: The error is that the scaled image height is 0. For example.  when source height is 14. scaled value is 1/16. and no rotate operation. then scaled height would be 0 as the result would be floored.

fields.name: XDST_LEN_TOO_LARGE_ERR_ST
fields.desc: The error is that the scaled image height is larger than (2^13 - 1).

fields.name: X_YUV420_RX_SCALE_ERR_ST
fields.desc: The error is that the ha/hb/x param in dma2d descriptor is an odd num when enable yuv420 rx

fields.name: Y_YUV420_RX_SCALE_ERR_ST
fields.desc: The error is that the va/vb/y param in dma2d descriptor is an odd num when enable yuv420 rx

fields.name: X_YUV420_TX_SCALE_ERR_ST
fields.desc: The error is that the ha/hb/x param in dma2d descriptor is an odd num when enable yuv420 tx

fields.name: Y_YUV420_TX_SCALE_ERR_ST
fields.desc: The error is that the va/vb/y param in dma2d descriptor is an odd num when enable yuv420 tx

fields.name: DATE
fields.desc: version register

1343045632.name: TX_CH%sDATA
1343045632.desc: The read and write  data register for CHANNEL%s by apb fifo access.

fields.name: CHDATA
fields.desc: Read and write data for channel %s via APB FIFO.

1343045648.name: RX_CH%sDATA
1343045648.desc: The read and write  data register for CHANNEL$n by apb fifo access.

fields.name: CHDATA
fields.desc: Read and write data for channel 0 via APB FIFO.

fields.name: TX_START_CH0
fields.desc: Set this bit to start sending data on CHANNEL%s.

fields.name: MEM_RD_RST_CH0
fields.desc: Set this bit to reset read ram address for CHANNEL%s by accessing transmitter.

fields.name: APB_MEM_RST_CH0
fields.desc: Set this bit to reset W/R ram address for CHANNEL%s by accessing apb fifo.

fields.name: TX_CONTI_MODE_CH0
fields.desc: Set this bit to restart transmission  from the first data to the last data in CHANNEL%s.

fields.name: MEM_TX_WRAP_EN_CH0
fields.desc: This is the channel %s enable bit for wraparound mode: it will resume sending at the start when the data to be sent is more than its memory size.

fields.name: IDLE_OUT_LV_CH0
fields.desc: This bit configures the level of output signal in CHANNEL%s when the latter is in IDLE state.

fields.name: IDLE_OUT_EN_CH0
fields.desc: This is the output enable-control bit for CHANNEL%s in IDLE state.

fields.name: TX_STOP_CH0
fields.desc: Set this bit to stop the transmitter of CHANNEL%s sending data out.

fields.name: DIV_CNT_CH0
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the divider for clock of CHANNEL%s.

fields.name: MEM_SIZE_CH0
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the maximum size of memory allocated to CHANNEL%s.

fields.name: CARRIER_EFF_EN_CH0
fields.desc: 1: Add carrier modulation on the output signal only at the send data state for CHANNEL%s. 0: Add carrier modulation on the output signal at all state for CHANNEL%s. Only valid when RMT_CARRIER_EN_CH%s is 1.

fields.name: CARRIER_EN_CH0
fields.desc: This is the carrier modulation enable-control bit for CHANNEL%s. 1: Add carrier modulation in the output signal. 0: No carrier modulation in sig_out.

fields.name: CARRIER_OUT_LV_CH0
fields.desc: This bit is used to configure the position of carrier wave for CHANNEL%s.1'h0: add carrier wave on low level.1'h1: add carrier wave on high level.

fields.name: AFIFO_RST_CH0
fields.desc: Reserved

fields.name: CONF_UPDATE_CH0
fields.desc: synchronization bit for CHANNEL%s

fields.name: DIV_CNT_CH4
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the divider for clock of CHANNEL%s.

fields.name: IDLE_THRES_CH4
fields.desc: When no edge is detected on the input signal and continuous clock cycles is longer than this register value, received process is finished.

fields.name: MEM_SIZE_CH4
fields.desc: This register is used to configure the maximum size of memory allocated to CHANNEL%s.

fields.name: CARRIER_EN_CH4
fields.desc: This is the carrier modulation enable-control bit for CHANNEL%s. 1: Add carrier modulation in the output signal. 0: No carrier modulation in sig_out.

fields.name: CARRIER_OUT_LV_CH4
fields.desc: This bit is used to configure the position of carrier wave for CHANNEL%s.1'h0: add carrier wave on low level.1'h1: add carrier wave on high level.

fields.name: RX_EN_CH4
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable receiver to receive data on CHANNEL%s.

fields.name: MEM_WR_RST_CH4
fields.desc: Set this bit to reset write ram address for CHANNEL%s by accessing receiver.

fields.name: APB_MEM_RST_CH4
fields.desc: Set this bit to reset W/R ram address for CHANNEL%s by accessing apb fifo.

fields.name: MEM_OWNER_CH4
fields.desc: This register marks the ownership of CHANNEL%s's ram block.1'h1: Receiver is using the ram. 1'h0: APB bus is using the ram.

fields.name: RX_FILTER_EN_CH4
fields.desc: This is the receive filter's enable bit for CHANNEL%s.

fields.name: RX_FILTER_THRES_CH4
fields.desc: Ignores the input pulse when its width is smaller than this register value in APB clock periods (in receive mode).

fields.name: MEM_RX_WRAP_EN_CH4
fields.desc: This is the channel %s enable bit for wraparound mode: it will resume receiving at the start when the data to be received is more than its memory size.

fields.name: CONTROLLER_RESET
fields.desc: To reset controller, firmware should set this bit. This bit is auto-cleared after two AHB and two sdhost_cclk_in clock cycles.

fields.name: FIFO_RESET
fields.desc:
To reset FIFO, firmware should set bit to 1. This bit is auto-cleared after completion of reset operation.
Note: FIFO pointers will be out of reset after 2 cycles of system clocks in addition to synchronization delay (2 cycles of card clock), after the fifo_reset is cleared.

fields.name: DMA_RESET
fields.desc: To reset DMA interface, firmware should set bit to 1. This bit is auto-cleared after two AHB clocks.

fields.name: INT_ENABLE
fields.desc: Global interrupt enable/disable bit. 0: Disable; 1: Enable.

fields.name: READ_WAIT
fields.desc: For sending read-wait to SDIO cards.

fields.name: SEND_IRQ_RESPONSE
fields.desc: Bit automatically clears once response is sent. To wait for MMC card interrupts, host issues CMD40 and waits for interrupt response from MMC card(s). In the meantime, if host wants SD/MMC to exit waiting for interrupt state, it can set this bit, at which time SD/MMC command state-machine sends CMD40 response on bus and returns to idle state.

fields.name: ABORT_READ_DATA
fields.desc: After a suspend-command is issued during a read-operation, software polls the card to find when the suspend-event occurred. Once the suspend-event has occurred, software sets the bit which will reset the data state machine that is waiting for the next block of data. This bit is automatically cleared once the data state machine is reset to idle.

fields.name: SEND_CCSD
fields.desc:
When set, SD/MMC sends CCSD to the CE-ATA device. Software sets this bit only if the current command is expecting CCS (that is, RW_BLK), and if interrupts are enabled for the CE-ATA device. Once the CCSD pattern is sent to the device, SD/MMC automatically clears the SDHOST_SEND_CCSD bit. It also sets the Command Done (CD) bit  in the SDHOST_RINTSTS_REG register, and generates an interrupt for the host, in case the Command Done interrupt is not masked. 
NOTE: Once the SDHOST_SEND_CCSD bit is set, it takes two card clock cycles to drive the CCSD on the CMD line. Due to this, within the boundary conditions the CCSD may be sent to the CE-ATA device, even if the device has signalled CCS.

fields.name: SEND_AUTO_STOP_CCSD
fields.desc: Always Set SDHOST_SEND_AUTO_STOP_CCSD and SDHOST_SEND_CCSD bits together; SDHOST_SEND_AUTO_STOP_CCSD should not be set independently of send_ccsd. When set, SD/MMC automatically sends an internally-generated STOP command (CMD12) to the CE-ATA device. After sending this internally-generated STOP command, the Auto Command Done (ACD) bit in SDHOST_RINTSTS_REG is set and an interrupt is generated for the host, in case the ACD interrupt is not masked. After sending the Command Completion Signal Disable (CCSD), SD/MMC automatically clears the  SDHOST_SEND_AUTO_STOP_CCSD bit.

fields.name: CEATA_DEVICE_INTERRUPT_STATUS
fields.desc: Software should appropriately write to this bit after the power-on reset or any other reset to the CE-ATA device. After reset, the CE-ATA device's interrupt is usually disabled (nIEN = 1). If the host enables the CE-ATA device's interrupt, then software should set this bit.

fields.name: CLK_DIVIDER0
fields.desc: Clock divider0 value. Clock divisor is 2*n, where n = 0 bypasses the divider (divisor of 1). For example, a value of 1 means divided by 2*1 = 2, a value of 0xFF means divided by 2*255 = 510, and so on.

fields.name: CLK_DIVIDER1
fields.desc: Clock divider1 value. Clock divisor is 2*n, where n = 0 bypasses the divider (divisor of 1). For example, a value of 1 means divided by 2*1 = 2, a value of 0xFF means divided by 2*255 = 510, and so on.

fields.name: CLK_DIVIDER2
fields.desc: Clock divider2 value. Clock divisor is 2*n, where n = 0 bypasses the divider (divisor of 1). For example, a value of 1 means divided by 2*1 = 2, a value of 0xFF means divided by 2*255 = 510, and so on.

fields.name: CLK_DIVIDER3
fields.desc: Clock divider3 value. Clock divisor is 2*n, where n = 0 bypasses the divider (divisor of 1). For example, a value of 1 means divided by 2*1 = 2, a value of 0xFF means divided by 2*255 = 510, and so on.

fields.name: CLKSRC
CCLK_ENABLE
LP_ENABLE

1342713876.name: TMOUT
1342713876.desc: Data and response timeout configuration register

fields.name: RESPONSE_TIMEOUT
fields.desc: Response timeout value. Value is specified in terms of number of card output clocks, i.e., sdhost_cclk_out.

fields.name: DATA_TIMEOUT
fields.desc:
Value for card data read timeout. This value is also used for data starvation by host timeout. The timeout counter is started only after the card clock is stopped. This value is specified in number of card output clocks, i.e. sdhost_cclk_out of the selected card.
NOTE: The software timer should be used if the timeout value is in the order of 100 ms. In this case, read data timeout interrupt needs to be disabled.

fields.name: CARD_WIDTH4
fields.desc:
One bit per card indicates if card is 1-bit or 4-bit mode.
0: 1-bit mode;
1: 4-bit mode.
Bit[1:0] correspond to card[1:0] respectively.

fields.name: CARD_WIDTH8
fields.desc:
One bit per card indicates if card is in 8-bit mode.
0: Non 8-bit mode;
1: 8-bit mode.
Bit[17:16] correspond to card[1:0] respectively.

1342713884.name: BLKSIZ
1342713884.desc: Card data block size configuration register

fields.name: BLOCK_SIZE
fields.desc: Block size.

fields.name: BYTE_COUNT
fields.desc: Number of bytes to be transferred, should be an integral multiple of Block Size for block transfers. For data transfers of undefined byte lengths, byte count should be set to 0. When byte count is set to 0, it is the responsibility of host to explicitly send stop/abort command to terminate data transfer.

fields.name: INT_MASK
SDIO_INT_MASK
fields.desc: SDIO interrupt mask, one bit for each card. Bit[17:16] correspond to card[15:0] respectively. When masked, SDIO interrupt detection for that card is disabled. 0 masks an interrupt, and 1 enables an interrupt.

fields.name: CMDARG
fields.desc: Value indicates command argument to be passed to the card.

fields.name: INDEX
fields.desc: Command index.

fields.name: RESPONSE_EXPECT
fields.desc: 0: No response expected from card; 1: Response expected from card.

fields.name: RESPONSE_LENGTH
fields.desc: 0: Short response expected from card; 1: Long response expected from card.

fields.name: CHECK_RESPONSE_CRC
fields.desc:
0: Do not check; 1: Check response CRC.
Some of command responses do not return valid CRC bits. Software should disable CRC checks for those commands in order to disable CRC checking by controller.

fields.name: DATA_EXPECTED
fields.desc: 0: No data transfer expected; 1: Data transfer expected.

fields.name: READ_WRITE
fields.desc:
0: Read from card; 1: Write to card.
Don't care if no data is expected from card.

fields.name: TRANSFER_MODE
fields.desc:
0: Block data transfer command; 1: Stream data transfer command.
Don't care if no data expected.

fields.name: SEND_AUTO_STOP
fields.desc: 0: No stop command is sent at the end of data transfer; 1: Send stop command at the end of data transfer.

fields.name: WAIT_PRVDATA_COMPLETE
fields.desc:
0: Send command at once, even if previous data transfer has not completed; 1: Wait for previous data transfer to complete before sending Command.
The SDHOST_WAIT_PRVDATA_COMPLETE] = 0 option is typically used to query status of card during data transfer or to stop current data transfer. SDHOST_CARD_NUMBERr should be same as in previous command.

fields.name: STOP_ABORT_CMD
fields.desc:
0: Neither stop nor abort command can stop current data transfer. If abort is sent to function-number currently selected or not in data-transfer mode, then bit should be set to 0; 1: Stop or abort command intended to stop current data transfer in progress.
When open-ended or predefined data transfer is in progress, and host issues stop or abort command to stop data transfer, bit should be set so that command/data state-machines of CIU can return correctly to idle state.

fields.name: SEND_INITIALIZATION
fields.desc:
0: Do not send initialization sequence (80 clocks of 1) before sending this command; 1: Send initialization sequence before sending this command.
After powered on, 80 clocks must be sent to card for initialization before sending any commands to card. Bit should be set while sending first command to card so that controller will initialize clocks before sending command to card.

fields.name: CARD_NUMBER
fields.desc: Card number in use. Represents physical slot number of card being accessed. In SD-only mode, up to two cards are supported.

fields.name: UPDATE_CLOCK_REGISTERS_ONLY
fields.desc:
0: Normal command sequence; 1: Do not send commands, just update clock register value into card clock domain.
Following register values are transferred into card clock domain: CLKDIV, CLRSRC, and CLKENA.
Changes card clocks (change frequency, truncate off or on, and set low-frequency mode). This is provided in order to change clock frequency or stop clock without having to send command to cards. During normal command sequence, when sdhost_update_clock_registers_only = 0, following control registers are transferred from BIU to CIU: CMD, CMDARG, TMOUT, CTYPE, BLKSIZ, and BYTCNT. CIU uses new register values for new command sequence to card(s). When bit is set, there are no Command Done interrupts because no command is sent to SD_MMC_CEATA cards.

fields.name: READ_CEATA_DEVICE
fields.desc:
Read access flag.
0: Host is not performing read access (RW_REG or RW_BLK)towards CE-ATA device;
1: Host is performing read access (RW_REG or RW_BLK) towards CE-ATA device.
Software should set this bit to indicate that CE-ATA device is being accessed for read transfer. This bit is used to disable read data timeout indication while performing CE-ATA read transfers. Maximum value of I/O transmission delay can be no less than 10 seconds. SD/MMC should not indicate read data timeout while waiting for data from CE-ATA device.

fields.name: CCS_EXPECTED
fields.desc:
Expected Command Completion Signal (CCS) configuration.
0: Interrupts are not enabled in CE-ATA device (nIEN = 1 in ATA control register), or command does not expect CCS from device;
1: Interrupts are enabled in CE-ATA device (nIEN = 0), and RW_BLK command expects command completion signal from CE-ATA device. 
If the command expects Command Completion Signal (CCS) from the CE-ATA device, the software should set this control bit. SD/MMC sets Data Transfer Over (DTO) bit in RINTSTS register and generates interrupt to host if Data Transfer Over interrupt is not masked.

fields.name: USE_HOLE
START_CMD
fields.desc: Start command. Once command is served by the CIU, this bit is automatically cleared. When this bit is set, host should not attempt to write to any command registers. If a write is attempted, hardware lock error is set in raw interrupt register. Once command is sent and a response is received from SD_MMC_CEATA cards, Command Done bit is set in the raw interrupt Register.

fields.name: FIFO_COUNT
fields.desc: FIFO count, number of filled locations in FIFO.

fields.name: TX_WMARK
fields.desc: FIFO threshold watermark level when transmitting data to card. When FIFO data count is less than or equal to this number, DMA/FIFO request is raised. If Interrupt is enabled, then interrupt  occurs. During end of packet, request or interrupt is generated, regardless of threshold programming.In non-DMA mode, when transmit FIFO threshold (TXDR) interrupt is enabled, then interrupt is generated instead of DMA request. During end of packet, on last interrupt, host is responsible for filling FIFO with only required remaining bytes (not before FIFO is full or after CIU completes data transfers, because FIFO may not be empty).  In DMA mode, at end of packet, if last transfer is less than burst  size, DMA controller does single cycles until required bytes are  transferred.

fields.name: RX_WMARK
fields.desc: FIFO threshold watermark level when receiving data to card.When FIFO data count reaches greater than this number , DMA/FIFO request is raised. During end of packet, request is generated regardless of threshold programming in order to complete any remaining data.In non-DMA mode, when receiver FIFO threshold (RXDR) interrupt is enabled, then interrupt is generated instead of DMA request.During end of packet, interrupt is not generated if threshold programming is larger than any remaining data. It is responsibility of host to read remaining bytes on seeing Data Transfer Done interrupt.In DMA mode, at end of packet, even if remaining bytes are less than threshold, DMA request does single transfers to flush out any remaining bytes before Data Transfer Done interrupt is set.

DDR mode selecton,1 bit for each card.
0-Non-DDR mdoe.
1-DDR mdoe.

fields.name: CARD_RESET
fields.desc:
Hardware reset.
1: Active mode; 
0: Reset. 
These bits cause the cards to enter pre-idle state, which requires them to be re-initialized. SDHOST_RST_CARD_RESET[0] should be set to 1'b0 to reset card0, SDHOST_RST_CARD_RESET[1] should be set to 1'b0 to reset card1.

fields.name: SWR
fields.desc: Software Reset. When set, the DMA Controller resets all its internal registers. It is automatically cleared after one clock cycle.

fields.name: FB
fields.desc: Fixed Burst. Controls whether the AHB Master interface performs fixed burst transfers or not. When set, the AHB will use only SINGLE, INCR4, INCR8 or INCR16 during start of normal burst transfers. When reset, the AHB will use SINGLE and INCR burst transfer operations.

fields.name: DE
fields.desc: IDMAC Enable. When set, the IDMAC is enabled.

fields.name: PBL
PD
fields.desc: Poll Demand. If the OWNER bit of a descriptor is not set, the FSM goes to the Suspend state. The host needs to write any value into this register for the IDMAC FSM to resume normal descriptor fetch operation. This is a write only .

fields.name: DBADDR
fields.desc: Start of Descriptor List. Contains the base address of the First Descriptor. The LSB bits [1:0] are ignored and taken as all-zero by the IDMAC internally. Hence these LSB bits may be treated as read-only.

fields.name: TI
fields.desc: Transmit Interrupt. Indicates that data transmission is finished for a descriptor. Writing 1 clears this bit.

fields.name: RI
fields.desc: Receive Interrupt. Indicates the completion of data reception for a descriptor. Writing 1 clears this bit.

fields.name: FBE
fields.desc: Fatal Bus Error Interrupt. Indicates that a Bus Error occurred (IDSTS[12:10]) . When this bit is set, the DMA disables all its bus accesses. Writing 1 clears this bit.

fields.name: DU
fields.desc: Descriptor Unavailable Interrupt. This bit is set when the descriptor is unavailable due to OWNER bit = 0 (DES0[31] = 0). Writing 1 clears this bit.

fields.name: CES
NIS
fields.desc: Normal Interrupt Summary. Logical OR of the following: IDSTS[0] : Transmit Interrupt, IDSTS[1] : Receive Interrupt. Only unmasked bits affect this bit. This is a sticky bit and must be cleared each time a corresponding bit that causes NIS to be set is cleared. Writing 1 clears this bit.

fields.name: AIS
fields.desc: Abnormal Interrupt Summary. Logical OR of the following: IDSTS[2] : Fatal Bus Interrupt, IDSTS[4] : DU bit Interrupt. Only unmasked bits affect this bit. This is a sticky bit and must be cleared each time a corresponding bit that causes AIS to be set is cleared. Writing 1 clears this bit.

fields.name: FBE_CODE
FSM
TI
fields.desc: Transmit Interrupt Enable. When set with Normal Interrupt Summary Enable, Transmit Interrupt is enabled. When reset, Transmit Interrupt is disabled.

fields.name: RI
fields.desc: Receive Interrupt Enable. When set with Normal Interrupt Summary Enable, Receive Interrupt is enabled. When reset, Receive Interrupt is disabled.

fields.name: FBE
fields.desc: Fatal Bus Error Enable. When set with Abnormal Interrupt Summary Enable, the Fatal Bus Error Interrupt is enabled. When reset, Fatal Bus Error Enable Interrupt is disabled.

fields.name: DU
fields.desc: Descriptor Unavailable Interrupt. When set along with Abnormal Interrupt Summary Enable, the DU interrupt is enabled.

fields.name: CES
fields.desc: Card Error summary Interrupt Enable. When set, it enables the Card Interrupt summary.

AI

fields.name: BUFADDR

fields.name: HALFSTARTBIT

Control for start bit detection mechanism duration of start bit.Each bit refers to one slot.Set this bit to 1 for eMMC4.5 and above,set to 0 for SD applications.For eMMC4.5,start bit can be:
1'b0-Full cycle.
1'b1-less than one full cycle.

fields.name: ENABLE_SHIFT
fields.desc:
Control for the amount of phase shift provided on the default enables in the design.Two bits assigned for each card.
2'b00-Default phase shift.
2'b01-Enables shifted to next immediate positive edge.
2'b10-Enables shifted to next immediate negative edge.
2'b11-Reserved.

fields.desc: Configures whether or not to open register clock gate.\\0: Open the clock gate only when application writes registers\\1: Force open the clock gate for register

fields.name: DATE
fields.desc: Configures the version.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_MST_ST
fields.desc: The current status of SPI0 master FSM: spi0_mst_st. 0: idle state, 1:SPI0_GRANT , 2: program/erase suspend state, 3: SPI0 read data state, 4: wait cache/EDMA sent data is stored in SPI0 TX FIFO, 5: SPI0 write data state.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SLV_ST
fields.desc: The current status of SPI0 slave FSM: mspi_st. 0: idle state, 1: preparation state, 2: send command state, 3: send address state, 4: wait state, 5: read data state, 6:write data state, 7: done state, 8: read data end state.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR
fields.desc: SPI0 USR_CMD start bit, only used when SPI_MEM_AXI_REQ_EN is cleared.  An operation will be triggered when the bit is set. The bit will be cleared once the operation done.1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_WDUMMY_DQS_ALWAYS_OUT
fields.desc: In the dummy phase of an MSPI write data transfer when accesses to flash, the level of SPI_DQS is output by the MSPI controller.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_WDUMMY_ALWAYS_OUT
fields.desc: In the dummy phase of an MSPI write data transfer when accesses to flash, the level of SPI_IO[7:0] is output by the MSPI controller.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FDUMMY_RIN
fields.desc: In an MSPI read data transfer when accesses to flash, the level of SPI_IO[7:0] is output by the MSPI controller in the first half part of dummy phase. It is used to mask invalid SPI_DQS in the half part of dummy phase.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FDUMMY_WOUT
fields.desc: In an MSPI write data transfer when accesses to flash, the level of SPI_IO[7:0] is output by the MSPI controller in the second half part of dummy phase. It is used to pre-drive flash.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FDOUT_OCT
fields.desc: Apply 8 signals during write-data phase 1:enable 0: disable

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FDIN_OCT
fields.desc: Apply 8 signals during read-data phase 1:enable 0: disable

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FADDR_OCT
fields.desc: Apply 8 signals during address phase 1:enable 0: disable

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FCMD_QUAD
fields.desc: Apply 4 signals during command phase 1:enable 0: disable

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FCMD_OCT
fields.desc: Apply 8 signals during command phase 1:enable 0: disable

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FASTRD_MODE
fields.desc: This bit enable the bits: SPI_MEM_FREAD_QIO, SPI_MEM_FREAD_DIO, SPI_MEM_FREAD_QOUT and SPI_MEM_FREAD_DOUT. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FREAD_DUAL
fields.desc: In the read operations, read-data phase apply 2 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_Q_POL
fields.desc: The bit is used to set MISO line polarity, 1: high 0, low

fields.name: SPI_MEM_D_POL
fields.desc: The bit is used to set MOSI line polarity, 1: high 0, low

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FREAD_QUAD
fields.desc: In the read operations read-data phase apply 4 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_WP
fields.desc: Write protect signal output when SPI is idle.  1: output high, 0: output low.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FREAD_DIO
fields.desc: In the read operations address phase and read-data phase apply 2 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FREAD_QIO
fields.desc: In the read operations address phase and read-data phase apply 4 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_DQS_IE_ALWAYS_ON
fields.desc: When accesses to flash, 1: the IE signals of pads connected to SPI_DQS are always 1. 0: Others.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_DATA_IE_ALWAYS_ON
fields.desc: When accesses to flash, 1: the IE signals of pads connected to SPI_IO[7:0] are always 1. 0: Others.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CLK_MODE
fields.desc: SPI clock mode bits. 0: SPI clock is off when CS inactive 1: SPI clock is delayed one cycle after CS inactive 2: SPI clock is delayed two cycles after CS inactive 3: SPI clock is alwasy on.

fields.name: SPI_AR_SIZE0_1_SUPPORT_EN
fields.desc: 1: MSPI supports ARSIZE 0~3. When ARSIZE =0~2, MSPI read address is 4*n and reply the real AXI read data back. 0: When ARSIZE 0~1, MSPI reply SLV_ERR.

fields.name: SPI_AW_SIZE0_1_SUPPORT_EN
fields.desc: 1: MSPI supports AWSIZE 0~3. 0: When AWSIZE 0~1, MSPI reply SLV_ERR.

fields.name: SPI_AXI_RDATA_BACK_FAST
fields.desc: 1: Reply AXI read data to AXI bus when one AXI read beat data is available. 0: Reply AXI read data to AXI bus when all the read data is available.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_RRESP_ECC_ERR_EN
fields.desc: 1: RRESP is SLV_ERR when there is a ECC error in AXI read data. 0: RRESP is OKAY when there is a ECC error in AXI read data. The ECC error information is recorded in SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_ADDR_REG.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_AR_SPLICE_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable AXI Read Splice-transfer.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_AW_SPLICE_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable AXI Write Splice-transfer.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_RAM0_EN
fields.desc: When SPI_MEM_DUAL_RAM_EN is 0 and SPI_MEM_RAM0_EN is 1, only EXT_RAM0 will be accessed. When SPI_MEM_DUAL_RAM_EN is 0 and SPI_MEM_RAM0_EN is 0, only EXT_RAM1 will be accessed. When SPI_MEM_DUAL_RAM_EN is 1,  EXT_RAM0 and EXT_RAM1 will be accessed at the same time.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_DUAL_RAM_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable DUAL-RAM mode, EXT_RAM0 and EXT_RAM1 will be accessed at the same time.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FAST_WRITE_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to write data faster, do not wait write data has been stored in tx_bus_fifo_l2. It will wait 4*T_clk_ctrl to insure the write data has been stored in  tx_bus_fifo_l2.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_RXFIFO_RST
fields.desc: The synchronous reset signal for SPI0 RX AFIFO and all the AES_MSPI SYNC FIFO to receive signals from AXI.  Set this bit to reset these FIFO.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_TXFIFO_RST
fields.desc: The synchronous reset signal for SPI0 TX AFIFO and all the AES_MSPI SYNC FIFO to send signals to AXI. Set this bit to reset these FIFO.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CS_SETUP_TIME
fields.desc: (cycles-1) of prepare phase by SPI Bus clock, this bits are combined with SPI_MEM_CS_SETUP bit.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_TIME
fields.desc: SPI CS signal is delayed to inactive by SPI bus clock, this bits are combined with SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD bit.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_ECC_CS_HOLD_TIME
fields.desc: SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_TIME + SPI_MEM_ECC_CS_HOLD_TIME is the SPI0 CS hold cycle in ECC mode when accessed flash.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_ECC_SKIP_PAGE_CORNER
fields.desc: 1: SPI0 and SPI1 skip page corner when accesses flash. 0: Not skip page corner when accesses flash.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_ECC_16TO18_BYTE_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable SPI0 and SPI1 ECC 16 bytes data with 2 ECC bytes mode when accesses flash.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SPLIT_TRANS_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable SPI0 split one AXI read flash transfer into two SPI transfers when one transfer will cross flash or EXT_RAM page corner, valid no matter whether there is an ECC region or not.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY
fields.desc: These bits are used to set the minimum CS high time tSHSL between SPI burst transfer when accesses to flash. tSHSL is (SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD_DELAY[5:0] + 1) MSPI core clock cycles.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SYNC_RESET
fields.desc: The spi0_mst_st and spi0_slv_st will be reset.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CLKCNT_L
fields.desc: In the master mode it must be equal to spi_mem_clkcnt_N.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CLKCNT_H
fields.desc: In the master mode it must be floor((spi_mem_clkcnt_N+1)/2-1).

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CLKCNT_N
fields.desc: In the master mode it is the divider of spi_mem_clk. So spi_mem_clk frequency is system/(spi_mem_clkcnt_N+1)

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CLK_EQU_SYSCLK
fields.desc: 1: 1-division mode, the frequency of SPI bus clock equals to that of MSPI module clock.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CS_HOLD
fields.desc: spi cs keep low when spi is in  done  phase. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CS_SETUP
fields.desc: spi cs is enable when spi is in  prepare  phase. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CK_OUT_EDGE
fields.desc: The bit combined with SPI_MEM_CK_IDLE_EDGE bit to control SPI clock mode 0~3.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR_DUMMY_IDLE
fields.desc: spi clock is disable in dummy phase when the bit is enable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR_DUMMY
fields.desc: This bit enable the dummy phase of an operation.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR_DUMMY_CYCLELEN
fields.desc: The length in spi_mem_clk cycles of dummy phase. The register value shall be (cycle_num-1).

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR_DBYTELEN
fields.desc: SPI0 USR_CMD read or write data byte length -1

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR_ADDR_BITLEN
fields.desc: The length in bits of address phase. The register value shall be (bit_num-1).

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR_COMMAND_VALUE
fields.desc: The value of  command.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR_COMMAND_BITLEN
fields.desc: The length in bits of command phase. The register value shall be (bit_num-1)

fields.name: SPI_MEM_WB_MODE
fields.desc: Mode bits in the flash fast read mode  it is combined with spi_mem_fastrd_mode bit.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FSUB_PIN
fields.desc: For SPI0,  flash is connected to SUBPINs.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SSUB_PIN
fields.desc: For SPI0,  sram is connected to SUBPINs.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CK_IDLE_EDGE
fields.desc: 1: SPI_CLK line is high when idle     0: spi clk line is low when idle

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CS_KEEP_ACTIVE
fields.desc: SPI_CS line keep low when the bit is set.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_AXI_REQ_EN
fields.desc: For SPI0, AXI master access enable, 1: enable, 0:disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CACHE_USR_ADDR_4BYTE
fields.desc: For SPI0,  cache  read flash with 4 bytes address, 1: enable, 0:disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CACHE_FLASH_USR_CMD
fields.desc: For SPI0,  cache  read flash for user define command, 1: enable, 0:disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FDIN_DUAL
fields.desc: For SPI0 flash, din phase apply 2 signals. 1: enable 0: disable. The bit is the same with spi_mem_fread_dio.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FDOUT_DUAL
fields.desc: For SPI0 flash, dout phase apply 2 signals. 1: enable 0: disable. The bit is the same with spi_mem_fread_dio.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FADDR_DUAL
fields.desc: For SPI0 flash, address phase apply 2 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.  The bit is the same with spi_mem_fread_dio.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FDIN_QUAD
fields.desc: For SPI0 flash, din phase apply 4 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.  The bit is the same with spi_mem_fread_qio.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FDOUT_QUAD
fields.desc: For SPI0 flash, dout phase apply 4 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.  The bit is the same with spi_mem_fread_qio.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_FADDR_QUAD
fields.desc: For SPI0 flash, address phase apply 4 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.  The bit is the same with spi_mem_fread_qio.

fields.name: SPI_SAME_AW_AR_ADDR_CHK_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to check AXI read/write the same address region.

fields.name: SPI_CLOSE_AXI_INF_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to close AXI read/write transfer to MSPI, which means that only SLV_ERR will be replied to BRESP/RRESP.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CACHE_USR_SADDR_4BYTE
fields.desc: For SPI0, In the external RAM mode, cache read flash with 4 bytes command, 1: enable, 0:disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR_SRAM_DIO
fields.desc: For SPI0, In the external RAM mode, spi dual I/O mode enable, 1: enable, 0:disable

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR_SRAM_QIO
fields.desc: For SPI0, In the external RAM mode, spi quad I/O mode enable, 1: enable, 0:disable

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR_WR_SRAM_DUMMY
fields.desc: For SPI0, In the external RAM mode, it is the enable bit of dummy phase for write operations.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_USR_RD_SRAM_DUMMY
fields.desc: For SPI0, In the external RAM mode, it is the enable bit of dummy phase for read operations.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CACHE_SRAM_USR_RCMD
fields.desc: For SPI0, In the external RAM mode cache read external RAM for user define command.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SRAM_RDUMMY_CYCLELEN
fields.desc: For SPI0, In the external RAM mode, it is the length in bits of read dummy phase. The register value shall be (bit_num-1).

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SRAM_ADDR_BITLEN
fields.desc: For SPI0, In the external RAM mode, it is the length in bits of address phase. The register value shall be (bit_num-1).

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CACHE_SRAM_USR_WCMD
fields.desc: For SPI0, In the external RAM mode cache write sram for user define command

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SRAM_OCT
fields.desc: reserved

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SRAM_WDUMMY_CYCLELEN
fields.desc: For SPI0, In the external RAM mode, it is the length in bits of write dummy phase. The register value shall be (bit_num-1).

1342750788.name: SPI_MEM_SRAM_CMD
1342750788.desc: SPI0 external RAM mode control register

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SCLK_MODE
fields.desc: SPI clock mode bits. 0: SPI clock is off when CS inactive 1: SPI clock is delayed one cycle after CS inactive 2: SPI clock is delayed two cycles after CS inactive 3: SPI clock is always on.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SWB_MODE
fields.desc: Mode bits in the external RAM fast read mode  it is combined with spi_mem_fastrd_mode bit.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SDIN_DUAL
fields.desc: For SPI0 external RAM , din phase apply 2 signals. 1: enable 0: disable. The bit is the same with spi_mem_usr_sram_dio.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SDOUT_DUAL
fields.desc: For SPI0 external RAM , dout phase apply 2 signals. 1: enable 0: disable. The bit is the same with spi_mem_usr_sram_dio.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SADDR_DUAL
fields.desc: For SPI0 external RAM , address phase apply 2 signals. 1: enable 0: disable. The bit is the same with spi_mem_usr_sram_dio.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SDIN_QUAD
fields.desc: For SPI0 external RAM , din phase apply 4 signals. 1: enable 0: disable. The bit is the same with spi_mem_usr_sram_qio.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SDOUT_QUAD
fields.desc: For SPI0 external RAM , dout phase apply 4 signals. 1: enable 0: disable. The bit is the same with spi_mem_usr_sram_qio.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SADDR_QUAD
fields.desc: For SPI0 external RAM , address phase apply 4 signals. 1: enable 0: disable. The bit is the same with spi_mem_usr_sram_qio.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SCMD_QUAD
fields.desc: For SPI0 external RAM , cmd phase apply 4 signals. 1: enable 0: disable. The bit is the same with spi_mem_usr_sram_qio.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SDIN_OCT
fields.desc: For SPI0 external RAM , din phase apply 8 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SDOUT_OCT
fields.desc: For SPI0 external RAM , dout phase apply 8 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SADDR_OCT
fields.desc: For SPI0 external RAM , address phase apply 4 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SCMD_OCT
fields.desc: For SPI0 external RAM , cmd phase apply 8 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SDUMMY_RIN
fields.desc: In the dummy phase of a MSPI read data transfer when accesses to external RAM, the signal level of SPI bus is output by the MSPI controller.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SDUMMY_WOUT
fields.desc: In the dummy phase of a MSPI write data transfer when accesses to external RAM, the signal level of SPI bus is output by the MSPI controller.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_WDUMMY_DQS_ALWAYS_OUT
fields.desc: In the dummy phase of an MSPI write data transfer when accesses to external RAM, the level of SPI_DQS is output by the MSPI controller.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_WDUMMY_ALWAYS_OUT
fields.desc: In the dummy phase of an MSPI write data transfer when accesses to external RAM, the level of SPI_IO[7:0] is output by the MSPI controller.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SDIN_HEX
fields.desc: For SPI0 external RAM , din phase apply 16 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SDOUT_HEX
fields.desc: For SPI0 external RAM , dout phase apply 16 signals. 1: enable 0: disable.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_DQS_IE_ALWAYS_ON
fields.desc: When accesses to external RAM, 1: the IE signals of pads connected to SPI_DQS are always 1. 0: Others.

fields.name: SPI_SMEM_DATA_IE_ALWAYS_ON
fields.desc: When accesses to external RAM, 1: the IE signals of pads connected to SPI_IO[7:0] are always 1. 0: Others.

1342750792.name: SPI_MEM_SRAM_DRD_CMD
1342750792.desc: SPI0 external RAM DDR read command control register

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CACHE_SRAM_USR_RD_CMD_VALUE
fields.desc: For SPI0,When cache mode is enable it is the read command value of command phase for sram.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CACHE_SRAM_USR_RD_CMD_BITLEN
fields.desc: For SPI0,When cache mode is enable it is the length in bits of command phase for sram. The register value shall be (bit_num-1).

1342750796.name: SPI_MEM_SRAM_DWR_CMD
1342750796.desc: SPI0 external RAM DDR write command control register

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CACHE_SRAM_USR_WR_CMD_VALUE
fields.desc: For SPI0,When cache mode is enable it is the write command value of command phase for sram.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_CACHE_SRAM_USR_WR_CMD_BITLEN
fields.desc: For SPI0,When cache mode is enable it is the in bits of command phase  for sram. The register value shall be (bit_num-1).

1342750800.name: SPI_MEM_SRAM_CLK
1342750800.desc: SPI0 external RAM clock control register

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SCLKCNT_L
fields.desc: For SPI0 external RAM  interface, it must be equal to spi_mem_clkcnt_N.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SCLKCNT_H
fields.desc: For SPI0 external RAM  interface, it must be floor((spi_mem_clkcnt_N+1)/2-1).

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SCLKCNT_N

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SCLK_EQU_SYSCLK
fields.desc: For SPI0 external RAM  interface, 1: spi_mem_clk is eqaul to system 0: spi_mem_clk is divided from system clock.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_LOCK_DELAY_TIME
fields.desc: The lock delay time of SPI0/1 arbiter by spi0_slv_st, after PER is sent by SPI1.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SLV_ST_END_INT_ENA

fields.name: SPI_MEM_MST_ST_END_INT_ENA
fields.desc: The enable bit for SPI_MEM_MST_ST_END_INT interrupt.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_INT_ENA
fields.desc: The enable bit for SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_INT interrupt.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_PMS_REJECT_INT_ENA
fields.desc: The enable bit for SPI_MEM_PMS_REJECT_INT interrupt.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_AXI_RADDR_ERR_INT_ENA
fields.desc: The enable bit for SPI_MEM_AXI_RADDR_ERR_INT interrupt.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_AXI_WR_FLASH_ERR_INT_ENA
fields.desc: The enable bit for SPI_MEM_AXI_WR_FALSH_ERR_INT interrupt.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_AXI_WADDR_ERR_INT__ENA
fields.desc: The enable bit for SPI_MEM_AXI_WADDR_ERR_INT interrupt.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_DQS0_AFIFO_OVF_INT_ENA
fields.desc: The enable bit for SPI_MEM_DQS0_AFIFO_OVF_INT interrupt.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_DQS1_AFIFO_OVF_INT_ENA
fields.desc: The enable bit for SPI_MEM_DQS1_AFIFO_OVF_INT interrupt.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_BUS_FIFO1_UDF_INT_ENA
fields.desc: The enable bit for SPI_MEM_BUS_FIFO1_UDF_INT interrupt.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_BUS_FIFO0_UDF_INT_ENA
fields.desc: The enable bit for SPI_MEM_BUS_FIFO0_UDF_INT interrupt.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_SLV_ST_END_INT_CLR
fields.desc: The clear bit for SPI_MEM_SLV_ST_END_INT interrupt.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_MST_ST_END_INT_CLR
fields.desc: The clear bit for SPI_MEM_MST_ST_END_INT interrupt.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_INT_CLR
fields.desc: The clear bit for SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_INT interrupt.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_PMS_REJECT_INT_CLR
fields.desc: The clear bit for SPI_MEM_PMS_REJECT_INT interrupt.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_AXI_RADDR_ERR_INT_CLR

fields.name: SPI_MEM_AXI_WR_FLASH_ERR_INT_CLR

fields.name: SPI_MEM_DQS1_AFIFO_OVF_INT_CLR

fields.name: SPI_MEM_MST_ST_END_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI_MEM_MST_ST_END_INT interrupt. 1: Triggered when spi0_mst_st is changed from non idle state to idle state. 0: Others.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_INT_RAW
fields.desc: The raw bit for SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_INT interrupt. When SPI_FMEM_ECC_ERR_INT_EN is set and  SPI_SMEM_ECC_ERR_INT_EN is cleared, this bit is triggered when the error times of SPI0/1 ECC read flash are equal or bigger than SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_INT_NUM. When SPI_FMEM_ECC_ERR_INT_EN is cleared and  SPI_SMEM_ECC_ERR_INT_EN is set, this bit is triggered when the error times of SPI0/1 ECC read external RAM are equal or bigger than SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_INT_NUM. When SPI_FMEM_ECC_ERR_INT_EN and  SPI_SMEM_ECC_ERR_INT_EN are set, this bit is triggered when the total error times of SPI0/1 ECC read external RAM and flash are equal or bigger than SPI_MEM_ECC_ERR_INT_NUM. When SPI_FMEM_ECC_ERR_INT_EN and  SPI_SMEM_ECC_ERR_INT_EN are cleared, this bit will not be triggered.

fields.name: SPI_MEM_AXI_RADDR_ERR_INT_RAW

fields.name: SPI_MEM_AXI_WR_FLASH_ERR_INT_RAW

fields.name: SPI_MEM_AXI_WADDR_ERR_INT_RAW

fields.desc: Set this bit to mask the first or the last byte in SPI0 ECC DDR write mode, when accesses to flash.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_RX_DDR_MSK_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to mask the first or the last byte in SPI0 ECC DDR read mode, when accesses to flash.

fields.desc: The delay number of data strobe which from memory based on SPI clock.

fields.desc: 1: Do not need the input of SPI_DQS signal, SPI0 starts to receive data when spi0_slv_st is in SPI_MEM_DIN state. It is used when there is no SPI_DQS signal or SPI_DQS signal is not stable. 0: SPI0 starts to store data at the positive and negative edge of SPI_DQS.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_CLK_DIFF_EN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable the differential SPI_CLK#.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_DQS_CA_IN
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable the input of SPI_DQS signal in SPI phases of CMD and ADDR.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_HYPERBUS_DUMMY_2X
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable the vary dummy function in SPI HyperBus mode, when SPI0 accesses flash or SPI1 accesses flash or sram.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_CLK_DIFF_INV
fields.desc: Set this bit to invert SPI_DIFF when accesses to flash. .

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_OCTA_RAM_ADDR
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable octa_ram address out when accesses to flash, which means ADDR_OUT[31:0] = {spi_usr_addr_value[25:4], 6'd0, spi_usr_addr_value[3:1], 1'b0}.

fields.name: SPI_FMEM_HYPERBUS_CA
fields.desc: Set this bit to enable HyperRAM address out when accesses to flash, which means ADDR_OUT[31:0] = {spi_usr_addr_value[19:4], 13'd0, spi_usr_addr_value[3:1]}.
